title: hot slaw
directions: Wash cabbage.
Add other ingredients including sausage.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: grandma cook's crumb cake
directions: Rub or blend first three ingredients together for crumbs.
Take out 1 cup for topping.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add corn, sugar and egg.
Add sufficient milk to make a good drop batter; fry in deep fat to a golden brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: graham cracker ice box dessert
directions: Beat sugar, butter until creamy, add eggs one at a time. Beat well and then add remaining ingredients.
Line pan with graham cracker crumbs, add mixture and cover with graham cracker crumbs. Mixture must stand 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and cherry.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into French fry size.
Dust with salt and pepper and seasoned flour.
Dip in beaten egg and milk.
Roll eggplant in cracker meal.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent towel.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and grated cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture.
Pour in a pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage and sausage soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cabbage, onion and potatoes to cook for about 3 minutes.
Add broth, bay leaf and seasonings to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook sausages for 15 minutes.
Remove soup and discard bay leaf.
Cool for awhile, then put in blender and liquify.
Return to saucepan. Add sausages and cream.
Heat on low for 5 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Put in order in a 13 x 9-inch pan the first 5 ingredients. Drizzle over this the sweetened condensed milk and chopped pecans. Cook in a 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix
together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix the
milk and egg together; add to the first mixture.
Add the remaining
ingredients.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse in cold water and drain.
Place in large serving bowl.
Add tomato, peppers, feta cheese and olives.

title: curious cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, eggs, water and butter.
Blend until smooth.
Pour one-half into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt the caramels with evaporated milk over low heat.
Pour over cake when removed from oven.
(Do not spread all the way to edges.)
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramels and sprinkle nuts over chips.
Pour rest of batter on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cool and top with topping. Refrigerate.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla on top of double boiler (not over heat); beat 1 minute with electric or rotary beater to blend. Place over boiling water and cook, beating constantly, till frosting forms stiff peaks, about 7 minutes (don't overcook). Remove from boiling water. Pour into mixing bowl, if you wish. Add vanilla; beat till of spreading consistency, 2 minutes. Frosts tops and sides of two 8 or 9 inch layers.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in blender or food processor until well blended.
Mixture may be used immediately or refrigerated for later use. Equivalent to one can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and cut potatoes as for thick French fries.
Place in 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with sugar and salt and sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg over the sugar.
Cover with pieces of butter. Twist slices of lemon over and place peel in with potatoes.
Sift flour evenly over potatoes.
Add water to mixture so that it can barely be seen.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are done and butter and sugar have made a thick syrup about the consistency of molasses, basting potatoes frequently with syrup.

title: no name pie
directions: Mix together. Put in oblong pan. Bake at 325 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: asian barbecue marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Marinate chicken, pork, flank steak or beef overnight in refrigerator, or at least 2 hours.
Use the marinade to baste the meat as it grills.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll in ball and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: dill bread(for bread machine)
directions: Place all ingredients, in order, in pan of bread machine. Process using "Basic" program. Remove from pan at end of cycle. Cool. Slice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add carrots and cook a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce and peas.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter and marshmallow cream in a large bowl. Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Beat until smooth and it begins to stiffen.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the
eggplant;
dice
and	boil until tender; then drain. Mix
in
saucepan, the celery, onion, sliced mushrooms and bell pepper;
saute
in butter until onion is clear.
Add mushrooms and milk; beat in eggs.
Add the eggplants; combine in buttered casserole.	Crumble toast on top and add remainder of sliced cheese
pound).
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: delicious squares
directions: Mix the first 3 items together.
Will be dry somewhat.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Blend together cream of chicken soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and oleo.
Add Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Fold into sliced potatoes and top with grated cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil in microwave.
Mix dry ingredients with oil. Stir well.
In medium bowl, pour crackers. Pour oil mixture over crackers and stir.
Let sit for 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand until syrup rises.
Beat eggs lightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Combine flour mixture to apples and sugar.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: greek style cheese ball
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature; cut into chunks.
In blender or food processor, process until smooth.
Reserve 1 tablespoon chopped olives and 1 tablespoon chopped green onion. Stir remaining olives, onion and basil into cheese mixture.
Shape into ball. Chill until serving time.
Sprinkle with reserved olives and green onion.
Serve with pita bread wedges or foccacia chips.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Fry sausage; drain well.
Place bread in bottom of large casserole dish.
Spread cooked sausage and cheese over bread. Beat eggs and milk together; pour over bread, sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.
Good!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add pineapple.
When it starts to jell, mix in remaining ingredients.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Egg whites should be folded into mixture. Bake in stem pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Make pie crust.
Pour eggs, syrup and sugar over the walnuts. Put this in the pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients on slow fire until it comes to a good boil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together well; drop by spoonfuls or spread on cookie sheet
and cut into bars.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well with a mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix together and bake at 475° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: molly's french toast
directions: Cook until bubbly: syrup, butter and sugar.
Pour this into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over syrup mixture. Arrange very thickly sliced bread (French or raisin) over mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour on top of bread and syrup mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cinnamon rice
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add carrots, celery and onion. Cover and cook for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally. Add rice, salt, cinnamon sticks, currants and water to pan and bring to boil over high heat.
Stir rice and lower heat to simmer. Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more. Remove cinnamon. Add 2 tablespoons butter and adjust seasonings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt with water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 15 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in buttered casserole for 1 hour at 300°.

title: party punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, pineapple and sherbet in a large mixing bowl.
Mix with electric mixer at low speed.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: shrimp and avocado salad
directions: Cut avocado lengthwise around middle. Remove pit with
a knife blade. Twist to separate halves and scoop out flesh and cut in wedges.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
cook until mixture boils. Add 2 tablespoons
minced
green	pepper,
1 tablespoon minced pimento and 1 tablespoon instant onion.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, adding syrup and milk.
Slowly add dry ingredients, which have been mixed together, pecans, vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook slowly at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato black walnut cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, nutmeg and allspice together.
Add to creamed mixture with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Use cream cheese frosting.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half in dish and congeal.
Spread on sour cream on top of congealed layer.
Pour remaining of first mixture.

title: arnie's mother-in-law's lemon chiffon cheese cake
directions: Melt margarine; blend with graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Reserve 1/8 cup mixture.
Press remaining mixture around sides and bottom of 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecan halves in an unbaked pie shell.
Mix and pour in rest of ingredients over pecans.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until done (35 to 45 minutes).

title: soft shell tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix the spinach dip and the ham and cheese and onion dip together.
Spread over tortilla shells very thinly. Roll up. Refrigerate until the roll is firm.
Slice and serve.

title: beef 'n' tator bake
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Pat meat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain excess fat.
Combine mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup shredded American cheese; spread cheese over meat.
Bake for another 30 minutes.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Bake for another 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Break off flowerets, discarding woody bottoms.
Wash thoroughly and parboil until slightly tender.
Drain and dust with flour.
Dip each floweret into beaten eggs, then roll in mixture of bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Fry in melted butter until brown on all sides.
Drain.
Serve while hot.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together egg, sugar, vanilla and melted butter (can add up to 3 tablespoons melted butter).
Stir in sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Add chopped apple, nuts, cinnamon and nutmeg and mix well.
Put in greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce and soda.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Bake in stem pan at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: dutch babies
directions: Mix together in a blender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat pie pan or large iron skillet with 1 teaspoon butter (in the oven). Pour batter into skillet or pie pan(s); bake for 20 minutes.
The pancake will be done when it is golden brown.
The pancake will puff up tall and fall when taken out of oven.
Drizzle melted butter and shake some powdered sugar over top.
Serve hot.

title: easy beef pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium skillet, brown ground beef, pepper and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Separate crescent rolls dough into 8 triangles.
Press on bottom and up side of a greased 9-inch pie pan; firmly press perforations and seal.
In a small bowl, combine 3 ounces of cheese and egg; stir to mix.
Spoon over dough.
Add to ground beef mixture; top with remaining 3 ounces of cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until edges of pie crust are golden brown.

title: sweet & sour kielbasi
directions: Cut Kielbasi into desired bite size.
Mix the above ingredients and pour over kielbasi and bake covered 25 minutes. Then bake 25 minutes uncovered.

title: tortillas
directions: Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt.
Add water, stirring with fork until dough leaves the sides of bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth (3 minutes).
Cover; let stand 15 minutes.
Divide into 12 parts.
Roll each into 7 to 8-inch circle on well floured board.
Cook on hot, ungreased skillet until bubbles are golden brown (2 minutes).
Turn and cook other side.
Stack and cover with towel to prevent drying.
Butter and cover with cinnamon.
Roll up for dessert, or fill with favorite Mexican filling.

title: strawberry pie crust
directions: Mix oleo and powdered sugar well.
Add flour and mix well. Pat into a 9-inch pie pan and flute edges. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with rolls.
Press firmly to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
Leftovers may be frozen to serve later.

title: laci pecsenye
directions: Use heavy cast-iron roasting pan.
Wash meat.
Melt shortening in pan over hot fire.
Deep fry pork in shortening.
Season pork with salt, pepper, garlic and paprika.
Drain meat.
Drain shortening from pan.
To pan, add boiling water and simmer.
Serve with rye bread.

title: suspiros de pili
directions: You will need paper cups.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in container of electric blender; process for 30 seconds.
Add vinegar and lemon juice; process 30 seconds.
Chill thoroughly before using.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard and salt.
Add half the vinegar and onion to dry mixture.
Beat on medium speed of mixer for 15 minutes.
Stir in oil, then remainder of vinegar.
Mix until well chilled.
Fold in celery seed.
Refrigerate.
Makes 3 pints.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, spaghetti mix and garlic.
Simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together.
Knead good.
Roll out thin and cut.
Let set at least 15 minutes.
Longer if you have time.
The dryer they are, the better they stay together.
Put in boiling broth.
Works good in fowl, beef or vegetable broth.

title: low-calorie zesty tomato dressing
directions: In a tightly covered jar, shake all ingredients until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate.
Shake before using.

title: fastnachts(doughnuts)
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and blend together until shininess leaves dough.
Roll on floured surface and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry in vegetable oil or shortening until golden brown, turning once.
Coat with sugar, powdered sugar or frosting.

title: crisp chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with salad dressing.
Coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Bring to a rolling boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and bring to rolling boil and cook 3 more minutes.
Pour into a shallow pan and let stand overnight.
Put in jars and seal next morning.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the bread.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Slice off top of bread and hollow out.
Cut leftover bread into bite size pieces and place around loaf.
Fill hollowed out bread with dip and enjoy!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add peaches. Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over top and cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs, flour, cinnamon and vanilla together until well blended.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in well oiled and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and pare apples.
Cut in small pieces.
Cover with water and cook until soft.

title: pat's copper pennies
directions: Layer cooked carrots in casserole dish with green pepper and onions.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots, pepper and onions.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator for at least 12 hours before serving.
Spicy, tasty side dish for any meal!

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix up Jell-O, cream cheese and pineapple.
Cut bananas into small chunks and add to mixture, then add chopped pecans and cherries.
Combine pineapple and cherry juices to make 2 cups of liquid; add to mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs and cooking oil.
Stir in pears and pecans.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into sugar mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, beating for five minutes.
Add cooking oil and beat 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour butter and all in grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Pour all together.
Top with broken up Cheez-Its.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough and place on cookie sheet.
Press with fingers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread this mixture on cooled cookie crust.
Top with any fruit (strawberries, peaches, pineapple, blueberries, etc.).

title: old fashion dumplings
directions: Rub shortening into flour.
Use milk to make a stiff dough (about 3/4 cup).
Shape into dumplings by rolling very thin and cut as needed. Cook about 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not stir or remove.
Cover until done.

title: gotompki
directions: Boil the cabbage whole in a big pot until tender.
When tender, cut the leaves off and cut the thick part out of the leaf.
While this is being done, fry onion in the chopped up fat back grease. Add the hamburger meat and cook.
When cooked, drain the grease out of the pan.
Add the grated carrots and the cooked rice.
When you have mixed all of the ingredients, get ready to make your rolls. Layer the bottom of a deep baking pan with some of the cabbage leaves.
Take a cabbage leaf.
Hold in the palm of your hand and put a spoonful of the meat mixture in it, then roll up the cabbage leaf and put in the pan you have lined with cabbage leaves.
When you have them all rolled and in the pan, put just enough water in to cover the bottom of the pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley. In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer 1/4 of the sauce, then 3 to 4 noodles, then 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat again.
Now add 1/4 of the sauce, 3 to 4 noodles and then rest of sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Let sit a few minutes before cutting.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop zucchini, onions and peppers in food chopper.
Add salt. Stir and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Put all other ingredients with ground zucchini mixture in large pan.
After bringing to boil, simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: eggplant parmagiana
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices. Dip each slice into beaten eggs, then crumbs. Saute in hot olive oil until golden brown on both sides. Place a layer of eggplant in a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the Parmesan cheese, oregano and basil. Top with several slices of Mozzarella. Then cover with 1 can of tomato sauce. Repeat two more layers ending last layer of sauce topped with several slices of Mozzarella. Bake in preheated 350° oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serves six.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Gently mix peaches, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into crust-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and make small slits in crust.
Seal crusts together and flute.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and pumpkin at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients, adding raisins last.
Bake in
ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost in pan.

title: asparagus with cucumber sauce
directions: Steam asparagus 5 minutes.
Rinse in cold water or refrigerate.
Blend peeled, seeded cucumber with mayo, sour cream, garlic and Worcestershire sauce until it has a creamy consistency. Chill.
Wrap asparagus spears with Prosciutto ham.
Arrange on plate and pour cucumber sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepper (or use sauce as dip).
Good with white wine.

title: brown meat and rice in consomme
directions: Pan brown meat.
Brown slowly on all sides in skillet, using a small amount of fat, if necessary.
Add green pepper, celery and onion and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add rice, consomme and water. Bring to boil; cover and simmer gently stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 4.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan or loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60
minutes until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding the egg last.
Drop from spoon into deep hot fat.
Hush puppies will float to surface and turn golden brown when done.
Drain.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with Frito Scoops.

title: brown stone cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until thoroughly mixed.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Add melted chocolate with warm water and vanilla.
Bake in layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper; toss lightly.
Spoon half of potato mixture into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole. Top with half of bacon and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli cheese soup(main dish or appetizer)
directions: Peel, slice and place potatoes in 6-quart pot with chopped onion.
Pour enough water to just cover top of potatoes.
Cut broccoli flowerets off the stalk.
Place flowerets only on top of potatoes.
Add salt to water.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites to form peaks.
Add sugar and beat slowly for 5 minutes.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put cookie sheets in oven.
Turn off heat at once.
Leave in oven overnight. Do not peek!

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Poach fish 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with melted butter.
For a different flavor, a teaspoon of mixed pickling spices may be added to the poaching water.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add beaten eggs, oil and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Will be a soft dough.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Using a teaspoon drop onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
One dozen to a sheet.
Press cookie down with a wet glass dipped in sugar.
Press lightly and evenly.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes on stove.
Cut stems, split and clean jalapeno peppers; save half the seed.
The more seed the hotter the salsa will be.
Wear rubber gloves.
Grind peppers and onions in food processor.
All should be approximately the same size.
Add to tomatoes; add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil; stir constantly. Cook 1 to 2 hours or until thick.
Set aside overnight in fridge. Skim off clear liquid; boil 1 hour.
Pack into sterilized jars. Cold pack, then boil jars 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift the first 8 ingredients.
Mix the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, pumpkin and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter 3/4 full into 3 greased and floured coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
After cooling, remove from cans and store.
Makes a great dessert when sliced and topped with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: easiest broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned at the top.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 cups cauliflower with cream sauce.
Top with Swiss cheese and bake until brown.

title: yogurt
directions: Bring milk just to a boil and remove immediately from heat; let cool until lukewarm (better to be too cool than too warm). Mix yogurt with one cup of the milk in separate bowl.
Add to remaining milk and mix well.
Pour into clean, covered glass container (such as large pickle jar).
Cover and place under several layers of blankets or a folded sleeping bag to retain heat for 12 to 24 hours.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion; add tuna and lemon juice.
Stir in flour.
Add cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Lower temperature.
Pepper to taste.
Open a can of biscuits and roll out each biscuit.
Place cheese in biscuit and fold biscuit around cheese.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 9-inch Corning Ware dish.
Place cheese filled biscuits on top.
Cook in 325° preheated oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Mix these ingredients alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add 1 cup cooked prunes (cut up) and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Cook at 250° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese together well.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add flour and pinch of salt, mixing well, but do not overbeat.
Pour
into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Combine can of pineapple, flour and sugar in pan and bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Remove from heat and add cherry pie filling. Let cool 15 minutes.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into crust and let cool in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip and serve.
Makes 3 pies.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichokes, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese and place in casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: hefezopf(yeast flat bread)
directions: Make a sweet leavened dough out of ingredients.
Form 3 strips (divide dough into thirds) and make a plait out of strings (braid dough).
Make a mixture of a little milk and one yolk.
Paint the dough with it and then decorate with almond splinters, fruit or something similar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, margarine, pineapple and coconut.
Beat well and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes and 5 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: healthy beef and barley bake(low-fat)
directions: Spray a large skillet with spray.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add meat and garlic.
Brown meat all sides.
Stir in broth, carrots, water chestnuts and basil.
Bring to boil.
Stir in barley; return mixture to boil.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven about 50 minutes or until beef and barley are nearly tender.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in zucchini and parsley.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: frog's eye salad
directions: Cook pasta 11 minutes. Rinse with cold water; drain well. In large bowl, beat reserved pineapple juice, milk, sugar and pudding 2 minutes. Gently stir in pasta and remaining ingredients; cover. Refrigerate at least 5 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, condensed milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together until blended well. Pour into pie shells and chill before serving. Yields 2 pies.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl until smooth. Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Remove and cool 5 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam.
Sprinkle
pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Beat egg and milk together in a small bowl.
Dip chicken in egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in rice.
Put cabbage in greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Pour all on top of cabbage; salt and pepper.
Mix soup, water, sugar and Accent together and pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smart stew
directions: Heat oil in bottom of a stew pot, toss beef in flour and brown in oil.
Remove beef and add diced onions to hot fat, sauteing until soft and golden.
Now add water, meat, papaya, potatoes, carrots, bay leaf, poppy seed and parsley.
Stir in mashed pumpkin and mix thoroughly, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Allow to simmer gently on stove top for 90 minutes, adding more liquid if stew becomes too dry.
Serve with a crisp green salad and hot baked bread.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
Beat eggs in different bowl.
Dip chicken in eggs then roll in dry mixture. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs together until creamy.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture; beat well.
Add applesauce, grated carrots, nuts and raisins if you like.
Blend well and pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° until done.
Spread with powdered sugar icing when cool.

title: chunky chicken and pasta soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or very large saucepan, cook the chicken in the olive oil over medium heat until the chicken begins to brown, about 5-6 minutes.
Stir frequently and
when done remove chicken to a plate.
Add 2 Tbsp. chicken broth to the pan.
Stir to combine olive oil with the juices in the pan.
Add onion and garlic and cook about 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the bell peppers and cook until peppers are tender, about 5 more minutes.
If liquid begins to evaporate add more broth.
Add remaining chicken broth and tomatoes, breaking up tomatoes with a spoon.
Add the cooked chicken and spices.
Stir to mix well and bring to a boil.
Stir in spaghetti and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard the bay leaf.
Serve.

title: bailey's original irish cream macadamia nut pie
directions: Using electric beater, cream the eggs, sugar, salt and butter. Add corn syrup and Bailey's.
Stir in chocolate chips and Macadamia nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add egg, shortening, orange juice and water.
Stir until just moistened.
Add cranberries, nuts and orange peel, folding to blend.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan. Cool slightly before removing.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: tailgate dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese. Add all ingredients and put in oven on low heat about 20 minutes.
Can be kept in slow cooker to keep warm.

title: pea soup
directions: Add all in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix and heat until hot; add sour cream last.

title: coconut cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening and 1 cup milk and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in baking powder. Add eggs and remaining milk and vanilla.
Pour in 3 paper-lined 10-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green peas supreme
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon in butter until lightly browned. Add the peas, onions, water, sugar, salt and pepper. Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender, about 10-15 minutes; drain.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: In a dish or Ziploc bag large enough to hold pork, combine oil, wine and garlic.
Add the pork, turning to coat it thoroughly. Marinate, covered, overnight in refrigerator.
Drain pork, discard marinade.
Grill pork and an oiled rack about 6-inches from fire for about 25 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 155°. Slice and serve.

title: all-bran brown bread(steamed)
directions: Mix bran, milk and raisins together; add molasses, then add sugar and flour which have been sifted with soda and salt.
Put mixture into greased pan.
Cover and steam 3 hours.

title: broiled market steak with savory butter
directions: Beat butter in a medium bowl until fluffy; gradually beat in lemon juice until well combined, then blend in dry mustard.
Mix in chives and parsley, distributing evenly.
Shape butter mixture into a roll about 1 inch in diameter; enclose in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Preheat broiler; place steak on rack of broiler pan about 4 inches from the heat.
Broil, turning once, for 6 to 8 minutes on each side for rare.
Increase time for medium or well-done.
When you turn the steak to broil second side, dot with about 1 tablespoon of the butter mixture. Place broiled steak on a carving board.
With a short pointed knife, cut the steak across the grain into several slices.
Serve slices on warm dinner plate.
Accompany with slices of herb butter.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: toasted baked potatoes
directions: Select potatoes uniform in size.
Pare potatoes and dry with a cloth. Brush with soft butter. Roll in fine cracker crumbs (saltines). Dip in slightly beaten egg, then roll in coarse cracker crumbs.
Lay in a well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 3 tablespoons of melted butter over top of potato balls.
Cover and bake until tender at 400°.
Serve piping hot.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter, then add sugar and egg yolks.
Beat until very light.
Add juice and grated rinds of lemons, flour and milk.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake slowly at 325° in pie shell about 1 hour or until brown.

title: apricot banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in bananas and lemon juice.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together.
Blend into banana mixture; stir in apricots.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix according to directions on package (better if left a little runny rather than too thick).
Set aside. Add the two sugars to the softened cream cheese; stir until smooth and creamy.
Fold whipped topping into cheese and mix until creamy.
Line rather large bowl with vanilla wafers and pour in pudding.
Combine the thawed strawberries with the thawed Cool Whip and spread over pudding.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover sliced cucumbers and onions with salt and ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
As ice melts, add more ice.
Do not pour off water.
Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Add allspice.
Drain water off cucumbers and add to vinegar and sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Line 8 x 8-inch cake pan or use prepared graham cracker crust.

title: yummies
directions: Melt chocolate in large bowl in microwave (2 minutes).
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Allow to cool.
Makes a lot; keeps well.

title: fried rice
directions: Add shortening and scramble eggs; saute bell pepper for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add ingredients until done; add rice and soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, then serve.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients slowly to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup of peanut butter; stir well.
Add vanilla and quick oats. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
Dice all vegetables.
Mix spaghetti and vegetables in large bowl; add dressing and turn all mixture over and over, mixing thoroughly.
Add cheese over top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; cook saffron rice as directed and mix first four ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use nacho chips and fixin's as desired. Serves 6.

title: ouejadas(portuguese coconut tarts)
directions: On floured surface, roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 3 1/2-inch circles.
Line 2 1/2-inch fluted tart shells with pastry circles; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and salt; stir in coconut.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons filling into each shell.
Place filled tart shells on baking sheet or shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tops are golden.
Cool.
Remove tarts from pans.
Makes about two dozen tarts.

title: lo-cal dip for veggies
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Cover and chill.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onion and celery. Cover and cook over medium-low heat until tender (15 minutes). Stir occasionally.
Blend in flour.
Add water, potatoes and salt; stirring constantly (increase heat).
Bring to a boil, turn down and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Stir occasionally.
Add milk, heat but do not boil (will curd).

title: easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Place cover on dish.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes or until chicken loses pink color.

title: fritos dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Place on serving dish.
Scatter remaining ingredients on top. Serve with chips.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together and spoon into 2 pie crusts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift first 4 ingredients.
Work shortening until light.
Add eggs and beat.
Slowly add flour mixture alternately with bananas, beating smooth after each addition. Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend together cornstarch and sugar.
Combine with water in saucepan.
Cook until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Allow to cool.
Spread berries in pie shell; slice, if desired.
Pour cooled Jell-O mixture over berries.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip at serving time.

title: herbed fish and tomato stew
directions: Wipe fish with a damp cloth.
Cut into serving pieces. Sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper.
In a deep frying pan or Dutch oven, cook onions in butter over medium heat until soft and bright green.
Add garlic, bay leaf, thyme, broth or wine and tomatoes with liquid.
Break tomatoes up with a fork.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until thick, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add lemon slices and fish.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat until fish is opaque and flakes when tested with a fork, 8 to 10 minutes.
Taste.
Add salt, if needed.
Serve fish in shallow bowls with tomato sauce spooned over.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon pitcher and add enough water and ice to fill completely.

title: rum balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except sugar.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.
Serves 2 1/2 dozen.

title: see's fudge candy
directions: Put chocolate or butterscotch chips, marshmallows, margarine, vanilla and nuts in a mixing bowl.
Do not cook.
Put sugar and evaporated milk in pan and cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 13 to 15 minutes.
Pour this into first mixture; stir until mixed.
Place in buttered pan.

title: hot mozzy
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 2 (2 cup) baking dishes. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers or Melba toast.

title: sniblings
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Melt cream cheese into sausage; set mixture aside.
Make biscuit dough per package directions. Roll dough flat.
Put sausage and cream cheese mixture on top of dough.
Roll it up like a jelly roll.
Slice and put the slices flat on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: egg scramble
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add flour, blending until smooth.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk; cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Set aside.

title: noodle-apple pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir in apple, raisins, noodles and butter.
Turn into a greased 1-quart baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle some cinnamon over top for color.

title: nanny's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add other ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dip-spicy appetizer
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In small saucepan, blend reserved juice, broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in pineapple.
Serve hot or cold with cocktail franks, ham cubes, bread sticks or vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Melt cheese in nonstick pan with the juice from the Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes very finely and add to cheese.
Let simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook hamburger until brown; drain.
Add 3/4 cup water and 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour. Add hamburger to cheese and let simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Add butter, sugar, flour, spice and salt.
Beat until creamy.
When cool, beat in milk, eggs and extracts.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir eggs into squash mixture. Add margarine.
Drop fritter batter by tablespoons onto greased griddle on skillet.
Cook until delicate brown; turn and brown on other side.
Serve immediately.
Serves six.

title: fish and chips(dominican)
directions: You will need a paper bag.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together (flour, sugar, soda and salt). Add to other ingredients.
Grease and flour the pan (9 x 14-inch) before putting mixture in.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: karen's crock-pot surprise
directions: Cut veal cutlets in half and pepper into strips.
Saute scallops in lemon juice and butter for five minutes.
Place veal, scallops, pepper and half of the peeled tomatoes (you may want to cut the tomatoes in half) in crock-pot.
Sprinkle basil, garlic to taste and Parmesan cheese on top.
Add a splash of wine, if you desire.
Cook on low for 6 hours.

title: velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda and buttermilk. Add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan. Any type of icing can be used.

title: pink arctic salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and add sugar.
Add cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple, walnuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into oiled loaf pan or mold.
Put in freezer overnight.
Great for holidays!

title: patience cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan. Punch holes. Bring to boil, sugar, milk and coconut. Pour over cake. Let cool. Put container Cool Whip over cake. Add another package frozen coconut on top of Cool Whip. Better if refrigerated before serving.

title: eggnog cheesecake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Beat cream cheese and sugar. Gradually add gelatin and eggnog.
Refrigerate until slighlty thick.
Beat whipping cream until peaks form.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and grated nutmeg.

title: healthy biscuits
directions: Combine skim milk and oil.
Pour all at once into self-rising flour.
Stir with spoon.
Pat out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: tacos botanas snacks
directions: Roll dough to fit into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes or until crisp around edges.
Let cool.
In small bowl, combine zucchini, refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread bean mixture and sour cream on baked crust.
Drizzle on salsa, top with cheese, green onions and olives.
Return to oven to melt cheese.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 dozen appetizers.

title: venison sausage
directions: Grind meat medium fine.
Combine with all other ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Keep cool.
May be stuffed in casings or made into patties.
Will keep frozen for 60 to 90 days.

title: old fashioned apple cobbler
directions: Mix boxes of pie crust mix; divide in half.
Place 1/2 in bottom of an oblong pan.
Save the other half for the top of the cobbler.
Peel apples and slice.
Add butter, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg on top of apples and mix together.
Sprinkle vanilla on top of ingredients.
Place mixture in the prepared oblong pan.
Roll out the other half of pie crust and place over top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°. Will serve about 12 people.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Saute onion and garlic slightly in oil; add sausage and cook for 15 minutes.
Then add spinach and cheese.
Cook until spinach is thawed and then another 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Let dough thaw and rise for a few hours.
Roll out oblong shape. Spread half of filling on each of two halves.
Roll up; put on greased sheet and let rise again for 1 hour.
Coat with egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame seed on top.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin pinon bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and spices.
Stir in pinons.
Mix together other ingredients; add flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hazelnut melting moments cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, lemon peel and egg yolk.
Blend well.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into balls (1 1/2-inch) and place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Make dent in center of each.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together and bring to a hard boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla flavoring.
Drop in teaspoon size drops onto wax paper until dry.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Combine peanuts and marshmallows.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and milk.
Blend together and spread in a 10 x 14-inch pan. Refrigerate.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake in greased jelly roll pan, 30 to 40 minutes.
Will be golden brown.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine peanut butter and oleo.
Beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in one cup morsels.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly on top.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Peel and slice peaches. Place in bowl. Pour 1 1/2 cups sugar over peaches. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Let set for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all together with fork until smooth.
If not stiff enough, add a little more flour.
Roll out on floured board.
Put flour over them.
Roll up and cut as desired.
If you want to dry you can, and they freeze good.

title: kountree kampinn saturday morning omelet
directions: I saute my vegetables in butter, then cool slightly before adding to egg mixture.
Mix eggs and vegetables together and pour into a lightly greased small casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with fresh chopped tomatoes.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Mix and bake white cake in 12 x 18-inch or sheet pan.
Cool and dump over to cardboard covered with foil.
With a large fork, poke 1/2 way through cake every inch or so.
Mix jello.
Before jello starts to jell, pour over top of white cake very evenly, soaking cake with jello.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Cover cake with Cool Whip and top with fresh sliced strawberries.
Ready to serve.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Then add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until loaves test done.
Cool 10 minutes before transferring from pans to wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: bean 'n bacon salad
directions: Combine beans, salad oil, 1/4 cup vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper; toss lightly.
Cover and chill.
Mix remaining ingredients, except bacon, greens and paprika.
Just before serving, drain bean mixture and toss with bacon.
Serve on crisp greens.
Top with a spoonful of egg mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon tea cakes
directions: In a bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients and beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 325° oven 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Low-fat and low cholesterol.

title: old fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until butter turns light golden brown.
Stir in boiling water and brown sugar. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Combine cornstarch, flour and salt in a bowl.
Gradually stir in milk. Stir milk mixture into butter mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat, stir small amount into the beaten egg yolks, blending well.
Immediately pour egg yolk mixture into hot mixture, blending well.
Cook 2 minutes more over low heat, stirring constantly.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes, pour into pie shell.
Cover and chill in the fridge.
To serve, whip cream, 1 tablespoon sugar and vanilla in a bowl until soft peaks form.
Spread over filling.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and water and mix well. Blend in flour and pecans.
Shape in balls or finger size bars. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
I turn up the heat for a few minutes to brown them.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
A good way to do this is to put the sandies in brown paper bag and add the powdered sugar and shake well.

title: cinnamon sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well (this makes a stiff dough).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions fine and cover with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain off water and again cover with boiling water; let stand for 10 minutes.
Place in a muslin bag and allow to drain overnight.
Combine the vinegar, salt and sugar; bring to boil.
Add pepper mixture and cook 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place berries, water and sugar in pan.
Put on stove on high until berries start to boil, then turn to low and cook about 10 minutes, or until berries are soft.
Remove.
Add Jell-O.
When cool, place in refrigerator; as mixture begins to set, add other ingredients.

title: greek salad
directions: Chop the tomatoes into medium cubes.
Sprinkle on some olive oil.
Crumble Feta cheese over it and add a few tablespoons capers. Toss and serve cold.

title: golden brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Stir in flour, then vanilla, then nuts.
Bake in greased pan (13 x 9-inch) until done.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: 7-layer dinner
directions: Brown and season ground beef.
Place in bottom of Dutch oven or large casserole.
Add one layer* diced potatoes, layer of celery and layer of sliced carrots.
Drain and reserve liquid from peas and add layer of peas.
Add layer of sliced onions.

title: ground beef pie(quiche)
directions: Let pie shell thaw at room temperature 10 minutes; prick bottom and side with fork.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: redfish court bouillon
directions: Cut redfish fillets diagonally into 2 1/2-inch strips.
In a one gallon heavy bottom saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Using a wire whisk, add flour, stirring constantly until dark brown roux is achieved.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until vegetables are wilted.
Add tomato sauce, blending well into roux mixture.

title: cream apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine eggs, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pineapple juice.
Cook slowly until mixture coats spoon.
Cool slightly.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: red rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in frying pan; pour fat back grease over. Cook on medium heat until almost dry.
Serve with fat back meat.

title: orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with paper.
Combine nut bread mix, orange juice, sour cream, orange peel and egg.
Stir by hand 50 to 75 times or until mix is moist.
Spoon batter in muffin pan; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove.
Serve warm.
Serve with warm marmalade.
Each muffin contains 150 calories, 10 g fat and 12 mg cholesterol.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract together; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour; mix well. Stir in chips and nuts by hand. Bake in 350° oven 9 to 11 minutes.

title: sissy's soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
While browning meat, cook mixed vegetables by directions on package.
Then add granules, corn, and English peas.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Then add browned meat.
Add tomato sauce and ketchup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: turkey hash
directions: Prepare turkey in covered roaster with enough water to make plenty of stock.
Put in celery, onion, bay leaf, red pepper and salt to season.
Steam for several hours until tender, but do not brown.
Remove stock and drain.
Allow to cool in covered bowl overnight.
Skim off fat; do not use.
Pull turkey from bones; cut in large bite size pieces.
Place in double boiler the turkey stock (for each 2 quarts of cut turkey, allow 1 quart stock).
To each quart stock, gradually add 1/2 stick butter and flour to make a paste.
Combine gradually to stock to thicken; add Worcestershire sauce and white pepper and more salt if desired. Serve hot with spoon bread or place in center of grit mould.
Also fine with waffles.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Do not drain cans.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar.
Combine all other ingredients.
Stir with spoon until all mixed together.
Use a bowl with lid.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep about 10 days.

title: peanut butter candies
directions: Mix peanut butter oleo and powdered sugar, chill in frig. Make into balls and place in freezer for 20 min. Melt parafin, choc-chips and candy bar over double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate, place on wax paper to cool. Keep in frig.

title: honey-dijon pork tenderloin
directions: Trim fat from tenderloins; sprinkle tenderloins with salt and pepper.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add 2 tenderloins; cook 10 minutes or until browned, turning occasionally.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Repeat procedure with remaining 2 tenderloins.

title: white boiled icing
directions: Boil to thread stage all ingredients, except egg whites, in saucepan.
Pour into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour slowly while beating at high speed.

title: inez's possum cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, pecans, coconut, vanilla and oats in bowl. Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in boiler.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour while hot over first mixture.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool before serving.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except banana and nuts.
Add those before serving.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate calories
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and chopped nuts.
Mix together well and pat into an 8-inch square pan to serve as crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa - hot
directions: Wash and cut stem off jalapenos.
Process the peppers, onions, garlic and tomatoes in blender just until vegetables are chopped fine.

title: corn pudding
directions: In blender, add all ingredients except 1 lb. pkg of corn. Blend well and pour in greased 11 x 14 baking dish.
Stir in the remaining frozen corn.
Bake in a moderate oven.
350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cukes, onions and peppers.
Add salt.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Put vinegar, sugar and spices in large kettle. Bring to boil, then add drained vegetables.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Pack hot into hot sterile jars; seal.

title: cabbage-apple slaw
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix together the yogurt, lemon juice and celery seed.
Add dressing to cabbage mixture in bowl; mix well.
Do not salt.
It will draw moisture from the cabbage.

title: puppy chow
directions: In small bowl, combine chips and butter.
Microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Place sugar in gallon size bag.
Add coated cereal and close bag tightly.
Shake until cereal is coated with sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put the rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the consomme in with the rice.
Place the chicken on the rice, skin side up.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour the mushrooms over top of the chicken.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over the chicken. Mix in a bowl the mushroom soup, chicken soup and celery soup. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil or lid and bake 30 minutes more.

title: candied yams
directions: Prepare and cook potatoes.
Cut each potato crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
In skillet combine brown sugar, butter, milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Add potato pieces.
Stir gently until glazed and heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: boiled macaroni with cheese
directions: Rule for boiling macaroni:
Bring to a boil the water to which salt has been added.
Slowly add macaroni and then continue to boil for 20 minutes.
At the end of 20 minutes, drain in a strainer and rinse by pouring over them 4 cups cold water.
To the 1 cup of prepared macaroni, add 1/2 cup of either cream or milk.
Reheat over a slow fire while stirring.
Place in a dish and sprinkle it with 1/2 cup or more to taste with grated cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into bite size pieces.
Lightly cook and drain. Mix other ingredients with 1/2 stuffing.
Put into casserole dish and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: amish breakfast
directions: Cook sausage and drain; cook potatoes and onions.
Drain. Layer meat, potatoes and cheese; heat milk.
Add eggs; beat good. Pour over casserole.

title: bill's strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix mashed bananas, strawberries and pineapple; add to jello mixture. Put half in dish or jello mold.
Let congeal about an hour.
Spread sour cream on it.
Add remainder of strawberry mixture and let congeal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let stand until bubbly. Combine next 5 ingredients and let cool.
Add yeast mixture, milk mixture, eggs and 4 cups of flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth.
Put into greased bowl; cover with waxed paper and damp cloth.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove part of dough and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cut, dip into melted margarine.
Fold and place on greased pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Can be partially baked, cooled and then put in freezer for later use.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and carrots together.
Add dry ingredients. Add flour and eggs and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use Foolproof Caramel Icing.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cut okra in pieces and fry in a little shortening until free of slime.
Set aside.
Put hot water to heat in a large pot.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, water, and salt together and pour into baking dish. Add cherries over the top. Bake at 350 degrees until batter is cooked.

title: potato salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and toss until well mixed.

title: cheese filled shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package; drain.
Cool in a single layer on waxed paper to keep shells from sticking.
Combine cheeses, eggs and spices.
Fill each shell with 2 tablespoons. Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put shells in, open side up.
Cover with rest of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: best ever cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients. Cover and chill several hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. Beat on medium speed.
Add zucchini, applesauce and orange juice; stir well. Combine next 5 ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or done when tested.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute vegetables over medium heat until soft.
Add flour and spices.
Stir well.
Remove from heat and add crawfish.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. May substitute shrimp for crawfish.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with miniature marshmallows.
Then mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour over marshmallows.
Then mix together strawberries, mashed and sweetened to taste, and jello.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Add dry instant pudding.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, butter and 10x sugar.
Drop by spoonful over cake.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes exactly.
Cake will be shaky when taken out but will set up.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt about 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add 2 1/2 cups of oatmeal and 1/2 cup peanut butter. Beat well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat greased iron skillet in oven at 450°.
Mix the ingredients; add mixture to hot skillet.
Bake to golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pan, cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add pasta sauce and sausage.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In a bowl, mix Ricotta, spinach, Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.
In a 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the cheeses, remaining lasagna and sauce.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until hot.
Uncover.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: mincemeat muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 18.

title: cheese cake ala helen
directions: Use a large bowl; mix everything, except sour cream until mixed in.
Now fold in sour cream.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Leave in oven to cool for 2 hours with oven door open.
(Don't grease and flour pan.)

title: buffet cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Slice carrots thinly; cook 15 to 20 minutes in water, covered. Melt butter and cook onion; stir in flour, salt, mustard, then milk.
Cook, stirring until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt. In 2 quart casserole, arrange layer of carrots, then cheese, ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over carrots/cheese.
Top with crumbs.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick butter.
Low boil onion, soups and chiles.
Line 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with 1/2 of tortillas.
Pour half of soup mixture over tortillas.
Layer half of chicken and then cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with jalapenos.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownie mix according to package directions. Stir in chocolate chips. Bake according to directions. Pour coffee over cooled brownies. Mix pudding. Crumble half the brownies into the bottom of a large glass bowl. Pour half the pudding on top. Crumble three candy bars on top of pudding and cover with half the whipped topping. Repeat layers.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in casserole until blended.
Bake, covered, until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch dish with croutons and cooked sausage. Beat eggs, mustard, milk, soup and mushrooms.
Pour over sausage. Must be refrigerated overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese last 20 minutes.

title: marinated poppy seed vegetable salad
directions: In blender or food processor, mix sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar and 2 tablespoons chopped onion; slowly add salad oil, then stir in poppy seed.
Pour over vegetables and cover.
Put in refrigerator for at least 24 hours (48 hours is recommended).

title: potluck pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until barely tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; toss to mix.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: tuscan pasta
directions: Place all ingredients except spaghetti in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 4 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Turn on HIGH. Stir in spaghetti.
Cover. Stir again
after 10 mins.
Cover and cook 45 mins. or until pasta is tender.
Garnish with basil and bell pepper strips.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well.
Use sugar until you can shape into small balls. Using a squirt bottle, place a dab of melted chocolate in candy cup.
Place ball in center.
Finish filling cup with chocolate.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with mayonnaise, relish and celery salt.
Blend until creamy and smooth enough to spread.
Lay out ham slices; spread with cream cheese mixture.
Place a pickle spear across on end.
Roll starting at the end with pickle spear; freeze slightly in covered container.
Slice into thin circles while still frozen.

title: banana walnut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; beat hard until light.
Add mashed banana.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir well until smooth.
Add walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ruby lemonade punch
directions: Stir concentrate into cranberry juice.
To serve, stir in diet pop and serve over ice.
Yield:
serves 8; 21 calories per serving.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread abundantly on flour tortillas and then roll each tortilla up tightly.
The cheese sticks them together.
These may be sent in lunches like this or cut in about 1-inch slices and served with mild salsa for parties.

title: texas red chili
directions: Combine chili powder, oregano, salt, cayenne pepper, cumin, tomato juice and chili beans with 4 cups of water in a large saucepan.
Simmer for several minutes.
Cook beef.
Drain and add to bean mixture.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in large bowl and set aside.

title: lovage seed bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients in bowl.
Leave in warm place until frothy.
Mix next four ingredients in another bowl.
Add yeast mixture and onion to flour mixture, kneading to make soft dough. Knead lightly on floured surface for 10 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place dough in a bowl, cover with damp cloth and leave to rise in a warm place for about 1 1/2 hours, until doubled in size.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls or loaves and place on baking tray or greased loaf pans.
Brush dough with a little water and sprinkle with the lovage seeds.
Leave for 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 400° for a further 5 to 20 minutes. Remove from pans to wire racks.
Yields 14 rolls or two (1 pound) loaves.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: copper pennies(carrots)
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water for about 10 minutes or just barely done.
Drain.
Cool.
Place in large bowl.
Add onions and green pepper.
Combine, blend remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps 1 week.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese; drain, then add tuna. Mix in cream of mushroom and celery soups and if you want peas.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes or until warm.

title: microwave mexican casserole
directions: Cook, crumble meat.
Add peppers and onions.
Cook on medium high heat until done (about 10 minutes).
Stir; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning, sauce, paste, water and chili powder.
Cook on medium heat until thickened.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, eggs and pepper.
In a glass dish (8 x 10-inch), put 2 tortillas down, half the meat mixture, then 1/2 sour cream.
Repeat and sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: marigold tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, and cheese. Pour into a 9 x 9 inch casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and spoon melted butter on top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze in ice cream freezer.
Refreezes well.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Put cake mix in big bowl; add 5 eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add oil, milk and water.
Stir all together.
Then add pistachio pudding.
Bake in a Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Spray a large saucepan with nonstick spray.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. Add flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Cut tortillas in half, then into strips like noodles.
Add to soup and simmer 5 minutes longer. I add 6 tortillas to soup in strips and simmer until dissolves. This thickens soup.
Just before serving, I add the other 6 cut into strips.

title: granny's hummingbird cake
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Beat butter until creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Add bananas, crushed pineapple (juice also), and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Add the nuts.
Pour into tube pan and bake 70 - 75 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Turn out onto cake plate.
Enjoy!!

title: the porters' green grape cobbler
directions: *Pick
them
while
they
are still small.
Walter said they will get too hard in 2 or 3 days.
tags: fresh little green unripe mustang grapes

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add green beans and sugar.
Simmer 25 - 30 minutes.
Also good in crock pot.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Spread in pan and bake at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: carla's green beans
directions: Season beans with salt, pepper, garlic powder and basil to taste. Wrap 10 to 12 beans with strip of bacon. Place in baking dish. Cover with liberal coating of brown sugar. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, using a good bit, but do not make brown sugar watery. Bake at 350° approximately 20
minutes until bacon is done.

title: florida sweet corn cakes
directions: Step One:
Combine all ingredients except flour and mix well. Add flour a little at a time until mixture blends.

title: spiced baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Stir well.
Pour into a slightly greased shallow 2 qt. baking dish.
Put bacon on top. Bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: kay's beans
directions: Cut half the
bacon
into 1/4 inch pieces.
Dice onion. Mix all ingredients
together
and
put in baking dish.
Cover top with remaining
bacon slices.
Bake in moderate oven until beans are bubbly and bacon is crisp.
Pour off excess fat.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil for 2 minutes the sugar, oleo, cocoa and sweet milk. Remove from heat.
Add the peanuts, nuts, oatmeal and vanilla.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix all together and freeze until icy.
(Takes about 1 full day.)
Before serving, add 2 quarts (two 2 liter bottles) of 7-Up.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and chill.
Freeze portion in mold for ice ring (optional).

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Brown pepper, onion and beef in oil, stirring occasionally.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
(Add water if too thick.)
Then add garlic and beans with liquid and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: janice's cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup pecans.
Sprinkle with chili powder.

title: beef marinade
directions: Place beef in marinade for 4 hours.
Time may not be increased.
Cut beef into chunks; skewer adding favorite fresh vegetables.
Grill and eat!

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with fruit.

title: rice elena
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all except Cheddar. Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: anise christmas cookies(cut outs)
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar
together until very light; beat eggs and add slowly to shortening and sugar mixture.
Add milk, one teaspoon at a time, stirring constantly.
Add anise. Sift four cups flour with
baking
powder.
Add
one
cup at a time; a little more flour
may be needed.
If so, add a little at a time. Take small
portions
of
dough;
roll out and cut into shapes. Bake in oven 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken  casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones, reserving chicken broth.
Make Stove Top according to package directions.
Add Pepperidge Farm mix and 1 cup of chicken broth.
Place half of mixture on the bottom of casserole dish.
Place cut up chicken on top.
Place both cans of chicken soup and 1 cup of chicken broth in a bowl and mix together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with remaining dressing mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Layer 9 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with whole graham crackers.
Prepare pudding by box directions.
Mix Cool Whip with the prepared pudding.
Pour over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Take frosting and dab on top of graham crackers as well as possible.
Heat in microwave for 50 seconds. Now that the chocolate has softened, continue to spread the chocolate across the top.
Chill in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Roll in flour until coated.
Brown in oil.
Place in crock-pot.
Add mushroom soup, onion and water. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, until tender.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix lemon jello and hot water, let stand until firm, then beat until fluffy.
Add celery, salad dressing, onion, pepper, hard-boiled eggs and corned beef.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Easy to prepare and refreshingly different.

title: hidden valley fried chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
