Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Remove chicken; shake off excess marinade.
Discard marinade.

title: cheesy santa fe corn muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with Pam.
In a large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a another medium bowl, stir together buttermilk, oil, eggs and
chilies. Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, stir to combine.
Add cheese, stir just until combined.
Spoon batter evenly into prepared muffin cups. Bake
in 350 degree oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes on a wire rack, serve warm.

title: kitchen potpourri
directions: Cut peels into thin strips and spread on baking sheet.
Dry in oven set on lowest temperature until peel is dry and brittle, approximately 3 1/2 hours.
Combine dried peel with spices and store in airtight jar.
Add a large spoonful of mixture to a pan of water.
Simmer over low heat.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, beans and onion.
Just before serving, add dressing and Fritos.
Mix well.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Put into bowl and add cream cheese, salt, pepper, Ricotta cheese, egg and basil.
In another bowl, mix together mushroom soup, milk, wine, seafood and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cook noodles until soft.

title: frosty golden punch
directions: Add water to frozen juices according to directions on cans. Add chilled apricot nectar and lemon juice.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet.
Carefully pour ginger ale down sides of punch bowl.
Yields 20-25 servings.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Prepare spinach according to package directions; drain. In a large bowl, mix spinach, soup, pepper, salt and sesame seeds. Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish; top with almonds. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beef and rice marinara
directions: Cook beef, mushrooms, onions, celery and green peppers over medium high heat in large skillet until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are crispy tender, stirring frequently.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Serve with cherries or substitute strawberries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add salt to squash and cook until tender in enough water to cover squash.
Pour off excess liquid and mash.
Add eggs, milk, onions, margarine and cheese.
Pour into casserole and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well (except cookies); put between baked, cooled cookies to make a cookie sandwich.

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine ground beef, cereal, cheese, garlic salt, pepper and egg. Use 1 tablespoon meat mixture to shape into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until no longer pink, turning meatballs halfway through. Drain on absorbent paper. Serve with sauce.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly and stir in lemon juice. Add other ingredients. Continue cooking slowly, in double boiler, until thickened (stir constantly). This is good for Eggs Benedict, broccoli, asparagus or cauliflower.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 2 x 1/2-inch strips and brown in hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and let simmer until tender.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; add to pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork.
Cook and stir until gravy thickens.
Add pineapple chunks, green pepper strips and onions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot rice and pass extra soy sauce.

title: hamburg delight
directions: Brown onion and hamburg.
Pour into greased casserole dish, add corn and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven until potatoes brown on top, about 1/2 hour.

title: mary's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers and let stand in ice water and salt three hours.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar and pour over cucumbers, etc.
Heat to boil.
Pour in sterilized jar and seal with hot lids.
Process ten minutes in a hot water bath.

title: carol's crab pate
directions: Heat soup over low heat. Remove from heat. Set aside. Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to soup, stirring well. Add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Spoon into an oiled 4-cup mold. Chill until firm. Remove from mold and garnish with parsley. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: crab spread
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine the mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Mix together well.
Add the cooled gelatin, celery, green onions, crab meat and mayonnaise.
Put in a serving dish and chill overnight to combine flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil, skin and cube the potatoes.
Add the pepper, onion, pimentos, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix bread (crumbled) with milk.
Put in bottom of baking dish.
Add potatoes, etc. Melt butter; drizzle over top.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In buttered 9-inch baking pan, layer broccoli, chicken cubes and cheese.
Combine gravy, milk, salt and pepper; pour over chicken broccoli mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: sunday brunch
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add potatoes to onion; cook until tender.
Layer, in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, potatoes, onion and meat.
Mix eggs as if you were going to scramble them.
Pour over mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 5 to 10 minutes so it cooks evenly.
Top with cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: quick oats cookies (no bake)
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and bring to boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan well.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut each of the roles in 4 pieces; drop into sugar.
Mix until coated; then drop into a greased pan.
Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand for 15 minutes.
Invert pan on wax paper covered rack.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time while beating in between each egg.
Add lemon extract and flour while alternating 7-Up.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, egg and pineapple and bake in a casserole for 20 minutes at 400°.
While this bakes, brown the cubed bread in the butter.
Add the buttered bread to the casserole and bake for about 30 minutes or until golden brown. Recipe may be doubled.

title: bacon cheese quiche
directions: Place pie shell into pie pan.
Fry and crumble bacon; sprinkle on pie crust.
Mix cheeses together and sprinkle over crust.
Beat eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour over bacon-cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then mix in sugar, oil and eggs and mix well.
Blend in rest of ingredients - carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts. Spread mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: suzie's broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer the above for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, water and butter to 260° or soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn; mix thoroughly.
Mold into balls.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole or 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until liquid is dissolved).

title: bacon wrapped chestnuts
directions: Slice bacon strips in half.
Wrap around a chestnut and stick a toothpick in to hold together.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Drain off grease.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate mixture for three days, taking it out to re-mix at least once a day.
On the fourth day, shape the mixture into small loaves, about 2 1/2 x 6-inches long.
Put on cookie sheet and bake overnight or 10 hours at 150°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together sweet potatoes, milk, eggs, vanilla, spice and salt until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake in rimmed baking sheet 60 to 65 minutes or until center appears set when pie is gently moved.
Remove to wire rack and cool before serving.

title: slum
directions: Fry side meat until crisp.
Combine grease from meat, potatoes, onions and roast beef with 6 cups of water.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add peas the last 10 minutes.

title: seashore lasagna
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Cook pasta, drain and cool.
Mix Ricotta, egg, spinach and Parmesan with salt to taste.
Stuff cooled shells with spinach mixture and place in casserole.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and layer of Mozzarella.
Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cornstarch.
Put into large mixer bowl the Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon juice and beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Beat about 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Save juice when draining.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add frozen orange juice and 2 cups juice from pineapple and oranges.
(If not enough juice, add water to make the 2 cups.) Add pineapple and oranges.
Add ginger ale.
Refrigerate.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites until they start to stiffen.
Add sugar, a little at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vinegar and salt.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto foil-lined baking sheets. Bake for 20 minutes; then turn off heat, but do not open the oven door.
Leave cookies in oven for 5 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Beat softened cream cheese with sour cream until well blended.
Add potatoes, beating constantly until light and fluffy.
Add milk, if needed.
Add seasonings to taste.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade french fries(baked not fried)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean and peel potatoes.
Cut them into quarter-inch lengthwise strips.
Soak strips in cold water for 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and blot dry.
Spread 1 to 2 teaspoons oil on a cookie sheet.
In a bowl, coat potatoes with 2 to 4 teaspoons oil.
Place strips on a cookie sheet and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Combine ingredients in Dutch oven.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer slowly 3 hours, covered, or until pork is very tender.
Skim off fat.
Stir with wire whisk until meat is shredded.
Salt to taste, if preferred.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Blend in half and half cream.
Gradually add flour.
Add flavorings and beat again.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Top with ketchup and A.1. sauce (spray pan with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix sour cream, instant pudding and milk until thickened. Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas in a large Pyrex dish.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients; mold into loaf in middle of 9 x 13-inch glass or metal pan.
Pour in 1 inch water.
Cover top with barbecue sauce.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in quarters.
Mix all dry ingredients in paper bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and then shake in bag. Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn only once.
When brown, sprinkle with parsley.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered container.
For each cup of cocoa, use 1/2 cup mix.
Stir in a little water to make a paste. Add 2/3 cup hot water.
Cook 2 minutes over medium heat.

title: pasta fagioli (vegetarian)
directions: In a large pan, add water, vegetables and spices.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
While this simmers, cook pasta and drain.
After about 1 hour, add 3 cans Northern beans (with juice) and tomato sauce with water.
Add pasta and stir gently.
Cook for an additional 30 minutes for everything to blend.
May be served with fresh Italian salad and garlic bread.
To add meat (optional), fry a pound of bacon and add to the vegetables and water in the beginning.
Ham is also a good meat to add.
Makes 8 to 10 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place block of cream cheese in bowl.
Use juice from fruit cocktail to soften.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts, if desired. Chill and serve.

title: country cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased pan (11 x 7 1/2-inch) and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Warm gravy, then mix all ingredients, except Parmesan.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This recipe can be increased by either placing all of this on top of frozen spinach souffle or by adding a package of frozen peas and carrots to the mixture.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add water.
Beat egg yolks and add to sugar mixture.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add margarine and lemon juice.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue.
Save egg whites for meringue.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Let dough thaw.
Heat oven to 400°.
Stretch dough thin, being careful not to tear.
Place pepperoni (3 or 4) in each roll. Sprinkle some cheese on pepperoni and pinch closed, careful not to tear.
Bake about 20 or 25 minutes, until golden in color.
Let cool a little.
Rub butter on top, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: mexican chicken strudel sticks
directions: Combine chicken, chilies, and cheese.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Mix until blended. Add the seasoned mayonnaise to the chicken mixture and mix well.
Spoon about 1/8 of the mixture onto one end of each tortilla.
Roll jelly-roll style. Fasten with toothpicks. Heat oil (about 1/2 inch deep)
in electric skillet to 375 degrees. Fry the chicken sticks until golden brown, turning as needed. Drain on paper towels. Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: microwave brown rice
directions: Cook margarine and onion (pepper if used) on High in microwave for 5 minutes.
Add soup and water.
Cover and boil 5 minutes. Add rice and cover.
Cook on Medium (4 or 5 power) for 15 minutes or until done.
Add mushrooms during last 5 minutes. Top with sausage links.

title: dad's goulash
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain.
Brown bacon until almost crisp.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until softened.
Add ground beef and cook through.
When beef is done, drain off grease from pot.
Add tomatoes, cinnamon, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat through; add drained pasta and heat through. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: a bit of heaven fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Ready to serve with any kind of fruit or as topping for pies or cakes.

title: easy oven barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in a roasting pan, then bake for 2 hours at 350° to 375°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Over low heat, melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla. When melted, stir in powdered sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking oil.
Cool.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Roll chicken strips and cheese (as much as rolls will hold) in the 8 rolls.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle each roll with a little more grated Cheddar.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: southern baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat with dry ingredients.
Place chicken skin side up in prepared pan. Lightly brush with margarine.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In 1-quart pan, heat chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and stir until coated.
Place lid over large bowl after adding powdered sugar. Seal securely and shake until coated.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine bananas and pecans, set aside.
Beat sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla at medium-high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into 2 waxed, lined loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix butter, eggs and sour cream in large bowl. Add whole corn, creamed corn and corn bread mix. Mix well. Pour into greased square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and pan-fry.
Pour off grease.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over sausage and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt the white chocolate 1 minute at a time on Low power in the microwave or melt in top of double boiler. Stir white chocolate after each minute. Should take 3 or 4 minutes to melt. Add the peanut butter to melted chocolate. Stir well. Add the sweetened condensed milk; stir. Have ready a small cake pan sprayed with Pam. Pour into pan. Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Remove from refrigerator and cut in squares.

title: chocolate mallow bars
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.
Mix marshmallows and nuts in large bowl. Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows and nuts; mix well. Divide mixture in half.
On waxed paper, sprinkle with confectioners sugar, shape each half into a roll approximately 8-inches long.
Chill several hours.
Slice to serve.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: three bean salad
directions: Rinse beans in cold water after opening cans.
Cook string beans until tender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add oil, salt and garlic powder to your taste.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Boil for 3 minutes: sugar, milk and butter.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal and cocoa.
Add nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: ranch microwave chicken
directions: On rack in large, shallow round microwave baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side down, around outside edge of dish.
Sprinkle with half of the salt, pepper and paprika.
Dot chicken with 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken, reversing center edge of thigh to outside and placing skin side up.
Add cauliflowerets in center of baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining salt, pepper and paprika; dot with remaining 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Cover only the cauliflowerets in center with plastic wrap; microwave on High 10 minutes more.
Rearrange flowerets and pour dressing over all. Cover chicken and cauliflower loosely with wax paper and microwave on High 10 minutes more.
To serve, spoon pan juices over all. Makes 4 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by large spoonfuls into deep fat fryer.
Fry until brown.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef in pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter with Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk; add vanilla last.
Grease and lightly flour tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine
sugar, salt, butter
and
milk
and
boil
six minutes.
Place chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and nuts in large bowl and pour boiling syrup
over the ingredients.
Beat until chocolate melts and pour into buttered
pan.
Let
stand a few minutes before cutting.
Store in tin box.

title: turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in a pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in a blender on high speed or 1 minute with a hand beater.
Pour into a pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and a knife inserted comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Preparation:
10 minutes, plus 30 minutes standing time.

title: lite apple slaw
directions: In large bowl toss cabbage, apples, walnuts and celery.
In separate bowl combine yogurt, applesauce, honey, vinegar and salt. Stir briskly.
Toss well with cabbage mixture.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with non-stick vegetable coating spray. Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Use an electric hand mixer for the batter, mixing remaining ingredients together all at once. Beat about 2 minutes.
Pour or spoon batter over pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add brown sugar, Crisco and buttermilk.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 35 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonful into hot oil.

title: peanut butter vegetable dip
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and milk.
Whip until creamy.
Serve as dip for celery, carrots, green pepper, etc.

title: appetizer
directions: Cut cold bacon slices in half.
Wrap slice of bacon around a date or water chestnut; secure with a toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: homestead breakfast
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and pour off some of the fat.
Add onion and fry for a few minutes.
Dice potatoes and add to bacon.
Fry until browned.
Beat eggs a little.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Pour over potato mix.
Cook, stirring often, until eggs are set. Very filling!
This will hold them until lunch.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt dorothy's cake brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Then add remaining ingredients (except nuts) and mix together.
Stir in nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If desired, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1 qt. casserole dish.
In 1 qt. sauce pan over med heat, cook frozen onion until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes; cook, stirring constantly till smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes, or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Yield:
4-5 servings.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar. Pour over margarine.
Add peaches, juice and all, over flour mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips; dust with peppered flour.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add drained mushrooms, onion and garlic and brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cover over low heat 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Pour into well-greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake at 350°. Makes 5 small loaves or 2 large loaves.
Small loaves bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Large loaves bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: potted cheese
directions: Finely grate cheese into a bowl. Add softened butter and mix well. Stir in Port or sherry, green onions, caraway seed, mustard and worcestershire sauce. Mix very well. Scoop mixture into a serving bowl. Cover with walnuts and press them into the mixture lightly. Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Serve with crackers or melba toast. It's very good.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix Bisquick, flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add whole eggs and can of beer.
Beat with electric mixer 1 minute until well blended.
Turn batter into a greased loaf pan (8 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: good fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Time 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Use medium heat.
This takes some time.) In another pot, melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Mix this together with the other mixture.
Remove from heat and beat with mixer for 5 minutes. Add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Pour into 3 buttered 8-inch pie pans or other shallow pans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Place in pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened. Pour in baked pie shell; let cool.

title: sour cucumber pickles
directions: Use small, whole cucumbers. Wash in cold water, wipe dry. Pack into hot, sterilized jars.
Fill with vinegar mixture.
Seal.

title: ginger crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in molasses. Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter and egg in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Cool until thick enough to spread, beating occasionally.
Great on Betty Crocker German chocolate pudding-in-the-mix cake mix.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and place blueberries over pineapple.
Pour the dry yellow cake mix over all. Melt oleo and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: banana marshmallow dessert
directions: Place banana and marshmallows in a bowl.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Pour into bowl.
Chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: oven barbecued chicken wings or small drumsticks
directions: Separate wings into little drumsticks by cutting apart.
Throw away third part (tip) of wing or buy very small drumsticks. Marinate for 2 hours. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

Baste often. Add 1 to 2 small cans pineapple chunks to the chicken and sauce when it's about half cooked. After cooking is completed, drain on a paper towel and serve. Delicious. Also great for a party.

title: stuffed celery stalks
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Stuff into celery pieces; sprinkle with peanuts.
Chill until you serve.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Mix all the ingredient and make a dough.
Cover and let stand for 15 min.
Preheat the oven on 300°.
Grease pizza pan with cooking spray.
Roll out the dough to make the crust.
Bake for about 10 mins or until it's light brown.
Flip it and let it bake the uncooked side.
When done spread pizza sauce and your fav. toppings and bake for 10 min.
And Enjoy!!!!!!!!

title: broccoli onion deluxe
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in salt water.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook until thick and bubbly. Reduce heat.
Blend in cream cheese.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix and pat flat in a well-oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: zucchini-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grate zucchini; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs until thick. Gradually beat in sugar
and
oil.
In
a separate bowl, sift 3 1/4 cups flour, baking
powder,
salt
and cinnamon.
On low speed, add dry ingredients
to egg mixture alternately with zucchini and wheat germ.

title: lemon lover cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. In a large bowl combine cake mix, lemonade, eggs and zest. Beat on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl often, then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: italian liver
directions: In a heavy skillet, in a scant 2 tablespoons of oil, start the onion cooking over low heat.
In a few minutes, add the green pepper, seeded and cut small.
Peel tomatoes; squeeze out most of their seeds and juice.
Cut small.
Add to onion mixture with salt, pepper and basil; cook until vegetables are soft.
Pat the sliced liver dry; thin it as needed.
Cut the strips in pieces about 1 1/2 inches long.
Remove the skillet of vegetables from heat, but keep warm in their pan.

In another skillet over high heat, saute the liver pieces, stirring and turning constantly so they don't stick, until they are cooked through, about 3 minutes. Dump the liver into the waiting skillet of warm onion, etc. Return it to heat for a minute to let flavors combine, then serve. Serves 4 generously or about 2/3 cup well drained, stewed, canned tomatoes.

title: hawaiian corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour 2 pans, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil
potatoes with peelings.
When potatoes are tender and cool,
peel and slice in quarters.
Place in baking dish. Put margarine
and sugars (white and brown) over top of potatoes. Cover with lid.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butter cookies(tea cakes)
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and stir together thoroughly.
Add the unbeaten egg yolk and vanilla, mix well.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to the cream mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir thoroughly.
Press through Cookie Maker.
Bake in quick oven until edges are brown (about 10 minutes).
Follow preparation instructions exactly or these will not turn out.
Quick oven is approximately 400°.

title: nuts and bolts(party mix)
directions: Melt the margarine and add Worcestershire sauce, onion salt, garlic salt and celery salt.
Put dry ingredients in large oblong pan and pour margarine mixture over all and stir thoroughly.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: coney island hot dogs
directions: Soak soup mix in hot water for 15 minutes.
Strain out onion pieces, reserving liquid.
Brown beef with onions in oil in a large skillet.
Add seasonings, ketchup and liquid from onion. Simmer together about 30 minutes.
Serve on wieners on buns.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Put 2 tablespoons crumbs on bottom of pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, 1 cup crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter together.
Spread in pan and along sides.
Beat until fluffy all of cream cheese.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Gradually add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° or until set, 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over cake and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Put in oven at 475° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Let cool. Garnish with cherry pie filling, strawberries, etc.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and add 1 large can pineapple and pecans.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
Can be frozen if wrapped well.

title: wheaties drop cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Stir in sour milk. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Add dry ingredients to mixture. Stir in nuts and raisins and fold in Wheaties. Chill dough and drop by teaspoon about 2-inches apart on greased baking pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, marshmallows together and let stand at least 4 hours or over night in refrigerator.
Add nuts, apples and whipped cream.. This keeps for several days.
I add fruit fresh to apples to keep them from turning dark.
Easy to double recipe. Serves 8.

title: chocolate meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Cover 2 cookie sheets with parchment; set aside.
Combine 1 egg white, 1/4 cup cocoa and 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Beat remaining egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, a little at a time, while beating until white are stiff and glossy.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture by thirds.
Fill pastry bag with mixture and pipe out cookies onto cookie sheets.
Each cookie should be about 1-inch wide.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes until dry texture.
Mix remaining 1 teaspoon cocoa and cinnamon; sprinkle over hot cookies.
(To make a pastry bag, use gallon plastic bag and cut off corner.)

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter
and milk in a saucepan and bring to boil for
minutes.
Put oatmeal, coconut, cocoa, vanilla and nuts in mixing bowl.
Pour hot mixture over these ingredients. Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper and allow to cool completely.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti noodles, butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put in bottom of pie pan.
Spread riccota cheese over top.
Pour spaghetti sauce over riccota cheese.
Sprinkle top with mozzarella cheese.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine the bread and pineapple and place in the prepared baking dish.
Mix the butter, sugar and eggs and pour over bread mixture. Bake until puffed and golden, about 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1-inch thick. Place in 2-quart casserole. Add salad dressing and butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and parsley. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until potatoes are tender. Serves 5.

title: spanish string beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Add hot sauce, spices and onion.
Bring to boil; simmer with beans.

title: vegetarian spinach pasta
directions: Bring 6 quarts of water to a boil with one tablespoon each of salt and olive oil.
Add pasta and gently stir.
Cook for approximately 10 minutes (do not overcook).
Drain a portion of the water.
Add 1 cup cool water to the pasta.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and vinegar in a buttered 4-cup measure; cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 12 to 15 minutes on Roast. Meanwhile, beat egg white in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form. Pour hot syrup into egg white, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Makes about 30 pieces.

title: apple betty pie
directions: Fill a large pie pan with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and melted butter. Put on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm. "Enjoy."

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat salad oil to 400° in deep skillet. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until browned. Turn once.

title: fried pie
directions: Mix well, but carefully, all ingredients.
Roll and cut into circles; put desired filling in center.
Fold crust over and seal with fingertips.
Fry in oil or shortening.

title: spicy pecan pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the pecans.
Beat with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Top with 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage apple stuffing
directions: To make stock, simmer giblets and neck of fowl until tender in a pint of water in sauce pan.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy made cobbler
directions: Mix well together.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in batter and then pour in fruit over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place sliced zucchini and onion in saucepan with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer (covered) for 5 to 8 minutes. Drain well. Place seasoning packet and stuffing mix in a bowl and add melted butter. Mix thoroughly.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O and hot water and let cool.
Add cream cheese, Dream Whip and crushed pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a mold and chill overnight.

title: ginger bars
directions: Bake in 350° oven.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and onion soup mix; place on first level of dish.
Mix together hamburg and taco seasoning; place on second level of dish.
Put shredded cheese over hamburg; melt in oven.
Cut up tomatoes and peppers.
Spread over dip.

title: curried cream soup with apples
directions: Chop the onion, celery and garlic.
Chop the tomatoes, reserving juice.
Peel and core the apple and dice.
Saute the onion, celery and garlic in butter, without browning.
Add the curry powder and cook 1 minute.
Add the flour to make a roux. Whip in the stock and bring to a boil.
Add the tomatoes and bay leaf.
Simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Remove the bay leaf and strain the soup.
Add the apple and bring to a boil.
Simmer a few minutes until the apple is cooked but still slightly crisp. Heat the cream and stir in; season.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cut up 1 head of lettuce.
This begins the bottom layer of the salad.
Continue with layers of celery, green pepper, onion and frozen peas.
Cover with Miracle Whip and sprinkle sugar over top. Add cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate and let it set up for 8 hours.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Add salt, pepper, Tabasco, thyme and bay leaf to sausage and saute in oil, then add onion and bell pepper and simmer.
Add garlic, rice, tomatoes, chicken stock and ham.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Add green onions for last 10 minutes of cooking.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cream
directions: Place the gelatin in a medium size bowl; cover with some of the cream.
Bring the remaining cream, the coffee and the sugar to a boil in a medium size saucepan.
Pour the gelatin mixture into the coffee mixture; stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Pour the mixture into a bowl; let it cool, stirring from time to time.
When cool, pour into cups.
Yields 5 servings.

title: hilda's mississippi caviar
directions: Mix and let stand.
Drain before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spread broccoli in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken meat next, then combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Combine crumbs with margarine and put over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream gravy
directions: Melt drippings.
Mix flour in jar with 1/2 of the milk.
Pour in with drippings.
Cook until bubbly.
Mix in rest of milk.
Cook until thick and creamy.
Use wire whisk to break up lumps and make it creamy.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Serve chilled dip on crackers.

title: lucille stock's potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in bowl.
Pour half melted oleo over potatoes and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix, except flakes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix flakes with 1/4 cup oleo.
Place on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except last 3.
Roll bread cubes with margarine.
Place on top of marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: garlic and mustard chicken(for four)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray glass dish with canola oil spray or rub lightly with oil.
Process (food processor) oil, vinegar, parsley, mustard and garlic to a paste.
Add pepper (and salt, if you like).
Dredge chicken in oil mixture and then in bread crumbs. Place in pan. Bake uncovered 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1 square chocolate in saucepan.
Blend sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, egg, graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts into butter-chocolate mixture.
Mix thoroughly and press into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or square 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Refrigerate while making filling.

title: diane's soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in a small amount of butter in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boiling temperature, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.
May also add green beans.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: stuffed baked pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop.
Make dressing of bread crumbs and seasonings.
Put dressing in the pockets of chops.
Brown on both sides.
Put in shallow pan and place in oven; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Layer in your punch bowl as follows:
tear apart 1/2 of cake for first layer, then 1/2 of pudding.
Next, one can cherry pie filling, then 1 can pineapple, 3 bananas (sliced) and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Start again with cake and a layer of each.
Top with chopped nuts.
Great for church dinners and family reunions.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Depends on how much cheese and chicken you like.

title: seven layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: carman lemon sponge
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat yolks; add to butter and sugar. Add flour, grated rind and juice.
Fold in beaten whites.
Pour into dish.
Place dish in pan of water.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine in large bowl with butter.
Add rest of ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in 3-quart buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: seafood pasta salsa
directions: Combine dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: peace of mind cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well in a large heart.
Using the 2 bent knees, gradually add the last 3 ingredients with more prayer (the more the better).
Put it in the oven of your best friend (Christ's hands) and let it bake until you hear a bell (the voice of your Savior).

Frost the cake with a thick layer of forgiveness. This is not an expensive cake to make, for all the ingredients can be found in 2 stores very near to your (your heart and your mind). It can be eaten daily for 7 days a week or longer, as it never gets stale unless you forget to mix in the last amount of prayer.
Also, this recipe can be doubled or tripled since the larger the cake the more others will have a chance to taste it and more people will want the recipe.

title: spinach squares
directions: Spread melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix spinach, eggs, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Mix in cheese and onion. Spread in a pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until set. Cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: eggplant mexicana dip
directions: Bake the eggplants at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, until blackened and soft.
Chop and mix in the rest of the ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks, flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour into saucepan.
Cook until thick (stir constantly).
Layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding twice in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat egg whites and top the pudding.
Bake until topping is slightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Cut up butter; add pineapple, coconut and sugar.
Mix well. Pour eggs over mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oleo.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes; stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swedish vegetable salad
directions: Drain liquids from beans, corn, pimento and peas.
Toss with dressing.

title: frothy lime punch
directions: In 1-quart pitcher, dissolve sugar in lime juice; stir in water.
Just before serving, pour lime mixture into punch bowl; add scoops of sherbet and Sprite.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: ragu italian bake
directions: Prepare noodles as directed; cut green pepper and onion in bite-size chunks into ground beef.
Cook, covered, until ground beef is brown.
(Slow cooking brings out flavor of pepper and onion.)
Heat Ragu in saucepan.
Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish with sliced pepperoni; sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted or bubbling.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening, vanilla, eggs and water.
Add flour (unsifted), baking powder and baking soda.
Beat thoroughly.
Add quick oats and mix by hand until blended.
Place small balls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 or 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pastry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients (not preserves) together.
Press 3/4 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread about 3/4 of the apricot preserves or jam over dough.
Roll out remaining dough and cut into strips.
Place in a crisscross design over top of the preserves.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: oreo cookie
directions: Crush cookies, all but 5.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Spread on top of cookies (do not mix).
Press with back of spoon.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Add Accent, dill weed and parsley flakes; mix well.
Refrigerate until cold or overnight preferred.
Makes large bowl full; serves 10 to 15 people.

title: delicious dip
directions: Cut beef into very small pieces.
Then stir all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.
Especially good on crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Dump all ingredients into a baking dish and mix together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If fresh corn is used, add 1/4 teaspoon salt.

title: seasonal jello
directions: Mix orange jello with 2 cups hot water and frozen orange juice.
Toss in mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Let set until hard.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour over jello mixture.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix cool whip, sour cream and jello together. Fold in remaining ingredients. Press into serving dish. Freeze overnight. Slice before serving. Serves 8.

title: batter-hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, 1/2 onion, 3/4 cup milk and eggs.
Set aside half mixture to use for batter.
Add remaining milk and onion to make hush puppies.

title: apple pecan cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Generously grease a 2 quart baking dish.

Arrange apple slices in an even layer in baking dish. In a small bowl, mix together, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup pecans. Sprinkle mixture over apples. In a medium bowl, mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. In separate bowl, whisk together egg, evaporated milk and melted butter. Pour milk mixture into flour mixture all at once, and stir until smooth. Pour mixture over apples, and sprinkle top with 1/4 cup pecans. Bake for 55 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of all liquid ingredients (Crisco, egg and buttermilk), except bananas.
Mix well.
Add rest of liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Add bananas. The more ripened the bananas the better!

title: chocolate easter nests
directions: Place chocolate in large casserole.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes until melted.
Stir in coconut and cornflakes.
Spoon onto waxed paper and form into nests.
Decorate each with 3 or 4 jelly beans.

title: crepes
directions: You will need small Teflon pan.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; cool thoroughly. Whip cream; fold into milk and marshmallow mixture. Add fruit and nuts. Place half of crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Add mixture and cover with remaining crumbs. Chill for several hours. Serves 12 to 15.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, apples and nuts.
Stir.
Place in ungreased baking dish 9 x 12-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve plain, with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hot toddy cold remedy
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer over low heat.
Stir occasionally to dissolve honey.
Serve hot.
Go to bed.
Don't get chilled if you perspire.
Use at bedtime.

title: shrimp soup orleans
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in a stockpot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add shrimp 5 minutes before serving.
As soon as they are pink and firm, soup is ready.
Serve with French bread.
Serves 4.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 1 1/2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine and bake for 20 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: candy cake
directions: In a saucepan, melt 2 sticks margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl with a mixer, mix eggs and sugar.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and vinegar together and add to eggs and sugar.
Add flour, baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla, gradually adding melted cocoa and water mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes cake is baking, make topping.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease cooking dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Add rice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soups and water together. Pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well. Add zucchini and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until bread springs back when lightly touched or tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: barbara's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender (about 30 to 35 minutes) in 4 cups water.
Pour off broth and save; let chicken cool and cut into pieces.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Boil or saute onions and peppers until soft.
In a greased (large) casserole dish, lay chicken in bottom.
Place cooked rice on top.
Put onions and peppers on top of rice.
Cover this with the cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, and beat.
Stir in nuts. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 large cake or 2 average cakes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add eggs and sugar, then add remaining ingredients. Pour this mixture into a pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marg king's strawberry preserves
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add alum.
Stir 6 minutes.
Cool until next day.
Put in jars cold and seal.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender. Put in deep-dish pie shell. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs- add sugar and mix well- add all other ingredients except milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer and top off with 1/2 gallon of whole milk.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, mix well. Drop dough by spoonfulls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Mix margarine and garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm.

title: basil tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes.
Sometimes I add sliced onions, artichokes, fresh mushrooms, etc.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water.
Drain; add onions and green peppers.
Mix and boil tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, salt, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve hot or cold.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Dissolve orange drink mix in pineapple juice.
Add instant pudding mix.
Stir until thick.
Fold in pineapple and oranges. Chill overnight.
Before serving, add apples and bananas.

title: berry special muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl. In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.

Fold berries into bowl of dry ingredients and then combine contents of two bowls together (if using cranberries, increase brown sugar to 1/2 cup). Fill paper lined or greased muffins tins and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken breasts on bottom of deep, stainless steel, nonstick pan.
Sprinkle the parsley, rosemary, garlic and pepper over chicken.
Place a layer of cut potatoes across chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of peas over potatoes. Pour wine over mixture.
Add another layer of potatoes and peas. Add more wine, if desired.
Place onion slices over mixture. Sprinkle with more pepper, garlic and rosemary.
Cover with foil. Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: pizza bread
directions: Brown hamburger
and cool. Grind cheese, onion and spam, mix with hamburger and sauces. Spread on bun or bread and broil until cheese bubbles.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Toss all together in large bowl.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, granulated and brown sugars, pudding and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Then beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar and half the flour. Beat until smooth. Add egg, shortening and remaining flour. Mix well.
Put out on floured pastry board and knead until smooth, adding enough flour to keep from sticking.
Put in bowl and let rise until double in size (should take about 45 minutes). Turn out on pastry board, knead lightly and shape into rolls. Place in pan and let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 good-sized rolls.

title: swans down angel food
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure and sift 4 more times.
Beat egg whites and salt with flat wire whisk.
When foamy, add cream of tartar and continue beating until eggs are stiff enough to hold up in peaks, but not dry.
Fold in sugar carefully, 2 tablespoons at a time, until all is used.
Fold in flavoring, then sift small amount of flour mixture and fold in carefully. Continue until all is used.
Pour batter into ungreased angel food pan and bake in slow oven.
Begin at 275°.
After 30 minutes, increase heat slightly (325°) and bake 30 minutes more.
Remove from oven. Invert pan 1 hour.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container. To serve, spoon 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls into mug and mix with hot water or milk.

title: fettuccine alfredo(microwave)
directions: Place hot, cooked fettuccine in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in light cream, sour cream, butter, green onions and garlic powder. Heat on full power for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through. Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: stir-fry
directions: Combine beef bouillon, cornstarch, garlic powder (1/4 teaspoon), ginger and water in a cup and mix thoroughly into a sauce; set aside.

title: mom's turkey or chicken hot dish
directions: Mix croutons, stick margarine and water together (lightly). Pour 1/2 into casserole.
Mix chicken or turkey, onion, mayonnaise, celery and salt together.
Put into casserole on top of last mixture.
Put remaining crouton mixture on top.
Beat 2 eggs; add milk.
Pour evenly over bread mix.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix together and set in refrigerator until set.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, layer half of the bread cubes.
Mix applesauce, 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg. Spread over bread cubes.
Layer remaining bread cubes on top. Drizzle Butter Buds on top.

title: hot russian tea
directions: Bring water
to boil and pour over tea bags.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags and set tea aside.
Combine pineapple juice
and next 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to
a boil.
Tie cinnamon stick and cloves in a cheesecloth bag.
Add spice
bag
and tea to juice mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Mix in beans in casserole.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's favorite bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix together.
Mix into a bowl or jar the chopped pepper, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over beans.
Marinate, covered, overnight. Stir a few times. Double or triple the recipe for large picnics.
Recipe alone serves 10 helpings.
Enjoy!

title: cool whip crazy cakes
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese in a bowl.
Gradually beat in milk until well blended and smooth.
Stir in whipped topping, mixing well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of mixture into each dessert shell. Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers. Have fun making different faces on the cakes.

title: remoulade sauce(serve over shrimp or crab meat)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
Pour over chilled cooked shrimp or white lump crab meat.

title: prunella cake
directions: Blend shortening with sugar and eggs.
Add chopped prunes. Stir in milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes; cool.

title: chopped broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 1/2 cup oleo (margarine); may use less.
Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, grating cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is browned, about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together butter, peanut butter, coconut and powdered sugar. Let stand for a few minutes. Shape mixture into balls. Melt paraffin wax & chocolate morsels in sauce pan. Dip ball into mixture and place on wax paper. Store in refrigerator.

title: greek cheese ball
directions: Process cheese until smooth.
Stir in olives, green onions and basil.
Shape into ball.
Cover and chill.
Serve with toasted pita wedges, chips or French bread slices.

title: glazed pineapple sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar, vanilla, salt and water until light and fluffy.
Add flour and stir in pineapple.

title: hazel's buttermilk cake
directions: Add alternately.
Fold in 6 egg whites (beaten).
Flavoring can be any kind you like.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook, drain and cool carrots.
Cut pepper and onion into rounds and mix with carrots.
Mix the next 8 ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more in the refrigerator.
Drain and serve.
This will keep for about 2 weeks in the juice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll canned biscuits in cinnamon and sugar.
Put nuts in angel food cake pan.
Layer biscuits all around.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water.
Boil for 2 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no name casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together until done.
Add soups, plus 2 cans full of water.
Add cooked potatoes.
Mix.
Place in casserole dish.
Make biscuits as directed on Bisquick box.
Cut to fit on top of casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are done.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and alum together in a bowl.
Heat to boiling the water, salt, oil and food coloring. Stir liquids into dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth. Store in airtight container.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 2 bread pans or a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Freeze.
Can be kept in freezer 6 to 8 weeks.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Baste meat with vinegar and water while cooking.
Just before done, baste with sweet and sour sauce.

title: wonderland pancakes
directions: Sift the baking powder, flour and salt together into a large mixing bowl.
Break the egg into the bowl; add the milk and stir until the batter is smooth (you can beat the batter with an eggbeater instead if you like).
Add the oil and mix.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Tilt the skillet to cover the bottom with the melted butter.
Pour in the batter a little at a time to make circles about 2 1/2 inches across.
Make sure you leave room between the pancakes; be careful because the batter spreads out.
When the pancakes are full of bubbles, but before the bubbles burst, turn them with a pancake turner.
Cook until the bottoms are browned.
Use the pancake turner to remove them from the skillet and stack them up on a plate.
Cover the plate loosely with aluminum foil to help keep the pancakes hot.
Melt another tablespoon of butter in the skillet and cook a second batch the same way and a fourth if you still have some batter left.

title: velma's soup roast
directions: Cover bottom of a roasting pan with foil, leaving generous overlap.
Sprinkle half of the package of onion soup mix over the foil and half of the can of mushroom soup.
Lay meat on top and sprinkle remaining dry soup and mushroom soup on top of meat.
Fold foil over top and seal airtight.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours or until meat is done.
This beef makes its own gravy.
I also bake it in a covered casserole dish.

title: devil crab
directions: Fix stuffing by directions on box but add 1 cup water, onion and pepper.
Add crab meat and mix.
Put in a baking dish and set oven for 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat cheese until fluffy and gradually add condensed milk.
Stir well until mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla extract and stir well.
Chill to 3 hours (don't freeze), then garnish top with cherry filling.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Mix thoroughly pumpkin, eggs, sugars, spice and milk.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Scatter with chopped pecans.
Bake 350° for 75 minutes.

title: hobo stew
directions: Boil beef until done.
Add diced potatoes, salt, pepper, onion salt and flour to thicken stew.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: scandinavian meat balls
directions: Soak
bread
in
water	and
make smooth.
Mix together beef, eggs,
salt,
pepper, oregano, garlic, parsley, 1/2 cup cheese and
undrained
bread.
Shape into small balls.
Brown meat balls evenly.
Drain off excess fat; add wine and 1/2 cup water.	Place mushrooms
and
green
peppers over meat balls. Cover
and	bake in	350° oven for 15 minutes.
Transfer meat balls to serving dish.

title: farm house sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening & sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream & vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture & blend. Roll out on floured board.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350 for 15-18 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking for sugar cookies. Frost after baked & cooled for holiday cookies.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat in a large bowl.
Add rice, onions, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and garlic powder.
Mix all these ingredients together with your hands.

title: rum balls
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate pieces over low heat. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, water, corn syrup, rum extract, butterscotch flavoring and vanilla extract. Fold in vanilla wafers and nuts. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls using 2 teaspoons of mixture for each. Roll in additional sugar. Store in an airtight container and refrigerate. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lazy pickles
directions: Wash and examine cucumbers.
If small, use the whole cucumber. If large, cut into strips.
Pack into glass jars.
Mix mustard, sugar, salt and spices together.
Add the vinegar slowly, stirring well.
Pour the brine over the pickles and seal.
Put in a cool, dark place.
After a week they are ready to eat and you don't have to heat the brine.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl; add water chestnuts, grapes, celery, almonds and pineapple.
Mix some of the mayonnaise with curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice. Add to the chicken mixture.
Tossing gently, add more mayonnaise as you need it.
Chill for several hours.
Spoon into nests of lettuce leaves.
Garnish with slices of lemon.
Serves 12.

title: venison summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then separate and roll in links approximately 2-inches thick.
Wrap in tinfoil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove from foil and bake on raised rack so meat is not in grease, for 35 minutes.
Then turn rolls and bake on other side for 35 minutes.
(Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes total time.)
Bake at 350°.
Cool and slice.
We often use meat casings instead of tinfoil.
Meat may be baked in casings.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together (better than you would a meat loaf).
Put into loaf pan and refrigerate overnight.
Next day slice, salt and pepper, flour and brown meat on both sides.
Put back in a baking dish with 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water or 1 package herb brown gravy mix and 1 jar Heinz mushroom gravy. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: premium parfait
directions: Mix until thickens.
Layer with crushed Nilla wafers and fresh blueberries.
Repeat layers in parfait glasses or in tall narrow serving glass/dish.
Can be served immediately or chill for soft cookies.

title: bill's shrimp creole
directions: You will need 1 wok.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and continue beating after each addition.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk. After batter has been well mixed, roll walnuts in flour and add to batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until done in a well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: italian-sicilian meat balls
directions: In large mixing bowl place chopped meat, garlic, parsley, bread crumbs, egg, eggplant, salt and pepper.
Make into small balls and fry in hot olive oil until brown on all sides.
Drain on rack then place in your favorite tomato sauce and simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: italian chicken
directions: Remove skin (optional).
Heat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken parts.
Dry on paper towel.
Put tomato juice in baking dish; roll chicken in tomato juice, leaving the chicken skin side down. Sprinkle spices over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Turn chicken over and bake an additional 1/2 hour or until tomato juice is absorbed by chicken in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage; drain.
Saute onion in skillet; set aside.
Combine meat, onion and all other ingredients, except noodles, in large stock pot.
Add about 1 can of water to ingredients.
Simmer (the longer, the better).
Cook noodles in water just until tender.
Combine with sauce; simmer no more than 20 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, drain and flake salmon, removing and discarding skin and bones.
Add potato, egg and garlic powder. Mix well.
Form into patties.
If necessary to make patties more firm (hold together), add some corn flake crumbs.
Fry in bacon drippings or vegetable oil at 350° for about 5 minutes on each side, or until brown.
Serve hot.

title: mexican luncheon
directions: Saute sausage, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook in a 2-quart dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots over high heat for 10 minutes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add onion and pepper.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight. Will keep for 2 or 3 weeks chilled.
Drain to serve as used.

title: cracklin' oat bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 20 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 lightly greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake in 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: egg and canadian bacon casserole
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place Canadian bacon over crescent rolls, followed by 1 cup Swiss cheese. Carefully drop eggs one at a time onto cheese and bacon layer. Be careful not to drop yolks. Pour cream over eggs and sprinkle remaining cup of Swiss cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Slice into squares and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Put small amounts of oatmeal in a blender until it turns to powder; measure out 5 cups oatmeal, not 5 cups powderized oats.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, peanuts and syrup.
Add raisins.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.

title: lacey's chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for an hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; prick with fork.
Bake at
for
45 minutes to 1 hour. Cut into lengthwise and
scoop
out potato. Set shells aside.
Mash potato; add margarine,
then
beat
in sour cream.
Season with salt and pepper. Stir
in
cheese and onion. Spoon mixture back into shells and place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 2
to 24 hours. Before serving,
bake,
uncovered, at 425°
for
minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: indoor-outdoor grill meat rub
directions: Use on barbecue and grilled meats.
Especially delicious on steaks!

title: coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows, nuts and milk.
Mix well.
Form into small balls. Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: parsnips
directions: Scrape parsnips; slice crosswise.
Cook until tender in salt water; drain and place in casserole.
Add sugar and butter.
Bake in moderate oven until liquid is low.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind peppers, pears and onions and squeeze juice out.
Add to vinegar, sugar, salt and turmeric.
Cook 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: spaghetti delight
directions: Cook spaghetti until almost tender.
Add cheese to melt.
Add 1 can water to soup.
Mix together with ham.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sausage genovese
directions: Fix Rice-A-Roni according to directions on package.
Alternate with browned sausage, drained and browned hamburger.
Pour tomato sauce over top; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
In bacon drippings, saute onions for 1 minute.
In large pan, put water, vinegar, sugar and 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Add onions and lettuce broken into bite size pieces.
Turn heat off, leaving pan on burner and toss ingredients to coat or wilt the lettuce.
Crumble the bacon and add to lettuce; toss again.
Serve slightly warm.

title: blue bayou dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and dry vanilla pudding.
Mix together.
In a trifle or punch bowl, layer pieces of cake, Cool Whip mixture and then blueberry filling.
Repeat layers until all is used, ending with blueberries on top.
Chill overnight or several hours before serving.

title: potato cucumber salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, celery seed and salt for dressing.
Set aside.
Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with part of potatoes, cucumbers, onion and dressing.
Make 2 or 3 layers. Sprinkle top with parsley.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine together and pat into glass 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle walnuts on top and pat them down.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and sugar until well blended.
Spread on crust.
Mix together pudding mix and milk and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and garnish with finely chopped walnuts.

title: jello shots
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and vodka. Pour into small disposable glasses or medicine cups.
Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine broccoli with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in small baking dish (9-inch square pan).
Sprinkle with crackers over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: judy's delicious spinach
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of boiling salted water; drain thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in medium, flameproof baking dish.
Turn off heat and stir in flour into butter until it forms a roux.
Turn heat onto low flame; add milk gradually, stirring continually until sauce thickens.
Add more milk if necessary.
Add mustard, grated white cheese and Parmesan slowly, stirring continually until smooth.
Add spinach; mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle
top with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Melt bacon fat in a large skillet.
Add cabbage.
Top with sliced potatoes.
Lay sausage on top; sprinkle with pepper.
Pour on boiling water.
Cover tightly and simmer over lowest heat for 50 to 60 minutes.
Add extra water if needed.
Serve with brown bread. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: In a glass 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in a 325° oven. Sprinkle crumbs; mix together with margarine in pan.
Spread evenly in bottom.
Add chips (as many or as little as you want). Add nuts, then coconut.
Cover with Eagle Brand milk (evenly over mixture).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown on top. Cool.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in honey, lemon, coffee, flour, soda and spices; beat until smooth.
Add berries and stir gently.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan; bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Remove from pan to cool.

title: mushroom chicken barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except the mushrooms and barley. Cover and simmer 1 hour until the chicken is tender.
Remove the meat from the bones and cut into pieces.
Return the chicken, vegetables and the reserved broth to the pan with the mushrooms and barley.
Bring to a boil, then simmer on low heat about 40 minutes until the barley is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: cabbage salad
directions: On a large cookie sheet sprayed with Pam, crumble the noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds. Stir and toast at 300° about 12 minutes. Cool slightly. In large mixing bowl, combine cabbage and chopped onions.

title: fish au gratin
directions: ABOUT 45 MINUTES BEFORE SERVING: Remove frozen fish fillets from freezer; let stand at room temperature 15 minutes to thaw slightly.

title: beef pomodori
directions: Brown meat and garlic in oil.
Add onions and cook 2 minutes longer.
Blend wine, tomato sauce, soup, broth, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer about 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in bowl. Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with crumbled Ritz crackers. Spread over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golden sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until golden.
Add cabbage and water.
Cover and cook for 7 to 8 minutes; drain.
Core and chop 1 apple.
Combine with sausage and cabbage.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Core and slice remaining apple and arrange over casserole.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, pepper and 1 tablespoon melted butter and pour over casserole.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut circles (3 inches round). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together; add eggs (one at a time).
Stir in flour, add apples and pecans.
Batter will tend to be thick.
Bake in well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage and zita bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, thoroughly brown sausage; drain fat.
Add next 3 ingredients; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over zita which has been placed in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake covered for 25 minutes.	Uncover and top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lazy daisy salad
directions: Fold in 3/4 of whipped topping with all other ingredients. Then spread remaining topping on this.
Sprinkle with coconut and chill.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Put chocolate chips on top.
Ready to eat.
Crunchy peanut butter can be used.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour. Add flavoring. Pour into well-greased and floured cake pan. Place in cold oven. Heat oven to 300°. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let set in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out onto rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugars and flour together in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add melted butter and pecans.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pie will come up in middle in oven and then fall.
