title: venison in barbecue sauce
directions: Brown bacon and remove from skillet. Brown venison and onions in bacon grease. Combine ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar in separate bowl; crumble bacon and add to mixture. Pour over meat. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: beef salpicon western-style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

In a skillet, brown meat and onion. Drain grease. Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Stir. Prepare mashed potatoes with water, margarine and milk; mix. Put meat mixture in baking dish. Spread corn evenly over meat.
Spread green chiles over corn. Spread mashed potatoes over chiles.
Sprinkle cheese over the potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes until cheese is melted.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chopped tomato on top.

title: pineapple cake
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. This cake does not have shortening.
2. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (or until done).
3. Cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish. Add corn, soup and cheese.
Mix.
Cook with Tater Tots.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Also good as a dip for raw vegetables.
Keeps nicely for several days, covered in the refrigerator.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pineapple pudding
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350° until brown and set (may take a little longer).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar. Dissolve jello in hot water. Add pineapple juice. Chill until partially set and then add other ingredients.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all together and pour over meat!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°. After 10 minutes, turn temperature down to 325° and bake for 20 more minutes.

title: baked corn casserole(iowa style)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in loaf cake pan or large casserole dish in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions in large skillet.
Remove excess fat. Spread uncooked noodles over meat.
Put cottage cheese on top of noodles.
Mix seasonings with tomato juice and pour over cottage cheese.
Stir slightly.
Put lid on skillet and over low heat until noodles are done (about 30 minutes).
Put cheese on top. Put lid on pan and turn off heat until cheese is melted.

title: chicken creole
directions: In hot butter, in large skillet, saute chicken until golden brown.
Remove pieces as they brown.
Add onion and garlic to drippings and saute until soft (approximately 5 minutes).
Blend in flour until smooth.
Remove from heat.

title: hawaiian pineapple fruit cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cake is better after standing one day.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients (except chili sauce and grape jelly). Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs and drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly is melted, stirring constantly. Add meatballs and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients. Add 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: debra's butter roll
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk; beat until stiff.
Roll out about 1/4-inch high.
Spread liberally with butter.
Top with sugar.
Roll like jelly roll.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
In saucepan, mix milk, sugar and vanilla; scald.
Pour over roll. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry-pie cake
directions: Put the one cup sugar with can of cherries and boil for a few minutes.
Make the rest like cake batter and put in square pan, well-greased.
Then pour cherries on top and bake in moderate oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: clam chowder(serves 6+)
directions: Barely cover potatoes, onion and celery with water in large pot.
Add parsley, tarragon, Nature's Seasons and salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in bananas and nuts.
Add flour, cereal, baking soda and salt; mix well.

title: party kibble
directions: Mix all ingredients except almond bark well in large bowl. Microwave almond bark in a zip lock bag, or bring a pot of water to a boil and turn off heat.
Put all the almond bark in the bag and seal up tight and put in water until all is melted.
Occasionally mix up bark through bag by squeezing unmelted chunks.
(do not open bag until ready to remove) After almond is completely melted cut a corner of the bag and drizzle over the mix and mix up well with a wooden spoon.
Then lay out flat on a long sheet of wax paper to cool completely (about 15 minutes in a cool area).
When cool just break up into smaller chunks and put into fresh zip locks.
It can be frozen and last a very long time.
It makes a great holiday gift when packaged.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine chicken, garlic, pepper, bay leaf, vinegar, soy sauce, vegetable oil and sugar in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer chicken to platter and keep warm.
Increase heat to high and cook sauce until syrupy, about 5 minutes.
Add snow peas.
Arrange pineapple around chicken on platter.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the zucchini and onion in salt water for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots and add to zucchini.
Mix Stove Top dressing and oleo.
Put half in bottom of casserole. Add vegetable mixture. Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: healthful date bread
directions: In a medium bowl combine dates and raisins.
Pour boiling water over mixture and set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
When date mixture is cool, stir in egg and vanilla.
Add the date mixture.
Stir until blended.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread batter evenly in a lightly greased 5 x 9 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook just until slightly firm, not mushy.
Then drain.
Add to potatoes, chopped onion, celery and boiled eggs.
Drain salad cubes and add to the potato mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise, just enough to coat salad mixture well.
Garnish with paprika.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf, place in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Twenty minutes before finished baking, brush with 2 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon of catsup and water mix.
Allow to set 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.

title: no bull ranch salad
directions: Mix together almonds, sesame seeds, cabbage, onions, noodles, chicken and oranges. Stir together remaining ingredients. Add to slaw mixture and chill for several hours before serving.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix
Cool
Whip
and Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice and stir well,
until
mixture thickens.
Crush vanilla wafers well and mix with 3
or 4 tablespoons butter and press mold in pie pans.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cherry frozen salad
directions: Mix together in order given.
Freeze them.
Slice into squares and serve.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add dry ingredients while continuing to beat.
Pour into jelly roll pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll up like jelly roll. Let cool.
Unroll and spread with filling and roll again.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain and put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add Worcestershire, onion and cheese.
Stir until cheese begins to melt.
Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle with crumbs mixed with melted margarine.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and brown sugar; mix well. Then add powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spanish rice
directions: Use a heavy skillet.
Heat oil; add rice, cook and stir with a fork, until rice is light golden brown.
Add chopped onions, celery, pepper and garlic.
Stir and beat well.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Stir well.
When hot and bubbling, quickly add boiling water.
Mix well.
Transfer to preheated greased casserole and cover.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Do not stir again or rice will be sticky.
When mixture is dry and fluffy, it is done.

title: fresh strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine pureed strawberries, half and half, 1 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate.
Beat eggs 2 minutes on high speed in a mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup of sugar and the salt to the eggs and beat for an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream.
Transfer to saucepan and cook over medium heat until mixture begins to simmer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Add Eagle Brand milk to custard and thoroughly combine chilled strawberry and custard mixtures using a wire whisk.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions for electric freezer.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: mary's baked beans
directions: Brown onion and green pepper with beef.
Add beans and chili sauce.
Add dipped bread pieces to hot ingredients, mix.
Place in large casserole dish and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Cook over low burner until right consistency.

title: pudding sauce
directions: Combine sugar, salt, and cornstarch, mixing well.
Add water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water or on very low heat, stirring constantly for about 15 minutes.
Add raisins after 10 minutes, and add vanilla after removing from heat.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Cut off top of melon and scoop out unseeded flesh.
Place 3 cups of flesh at a time in a blender.
Process until smooth (seeds will float).
Pour puree through a wire mesh strainer.
Discard pulp.
Repeat process until you have 15 cups of juice.
Combine melon juice, orange and lemon juice.
Chill at least 2 hours. Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Yields approximately 20 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla instant pudding mix with cold milk.
Then mix whipped cream with sour cream.
Then add all together; layer bananas, then vanilla wafers, then pudding mix.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes and place in saucepan with 1/4 cup butter.
Heat over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring often.
Place vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Add noodle twisties and mix well.

title: creamed cucumber slices
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to taste; pour over cucumbers and onions. Stir well.

title: french toast
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Dip 1/2 slice of white bread in batter, then in deep fat.
Brown, drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In large bowl, stir dry ingredients until thoroughly blended. Cut in butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until crumbly.
In a separate bowl, beat egg slightly and mix with buttermilk; stir in dry ingredients and raisins until blended.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth (2 to 3 minutes).

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix water with sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from stove and add the pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
In a blender, blend the bananas.
Mix the sugar syrup mixture with bananas.
Place in plastic containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, put in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over this.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolve.
Gradually add milk and mix well.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer read 248° (firm ball stage).
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla until well blended.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonsful onto foil lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in a microwave-safe bowl or double boiler.
Drizzle over each cluster.
Cool.
Yield:
about 4 doz.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix cream cheese with butter until blended.
Beat in sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind and vanilla.
Slowly stir in flour mixture until blended.
Batter will be very heavy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix all ingredients. Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes, until firm and golden in color.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Add enough mayonnaise to mix.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Lightly toast each split muffin.
Melt 2 to 3 pats of butter into each muffin.
Top each muffin with 4 ham slices; heat through. Top each stack with poached egg.
Spoon cheese sauce over each stack.
Serves 4.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Make serving size of 4 following directions of instant potatoes.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put crushed potato chips on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini spaghetti
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and pepper in margarine until tender. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Layer zucchini, onion and pepper mixture with spaghetti sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbling around the edges.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash thin in cubes.
Steam in saucepan with 2 tablespoons water and 1 tablespoon butter until soft.
If lots of water when done, drain.
Make stuffing as directed on package. Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until browned and cheeses are melted (25 to 30 minutes).

title: fruit salad
directions: Put reserved juices into a small saucepan.
Add orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and cornstarch and cook over low heat until it boils for about 2 minutes.
Pour over the cut-up fruit and cover. Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt
butter;
mix
with brown sugar and eggs.	Stir in flour, nuts
and
chocolate chips.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy peach nut bread
directions: Using solid shortening, generously grease and flour 9 x 5 or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.

title: sugar free vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in freezer according to manufacturers instructions.

title: hershey's chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt
chocolates
over low heat.
Cool and add vanilla. Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add chocolate mixture to
butter.
Add
flour
and soda mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan and
loaf pan or 1 large sheet pan.
Bake at 300° to
350° for
approximately
1 hour.
Check with toothpick or finger press after 45 minutes.
Cool before taking from pans.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix ingredients together except for cheese. Place in a baking dish and top with cheese. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Place sliced apples in Pyrex pie plate or 8-inch square dish. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon on apples.
Make a paste of the remaining ingredients.
Spread paste over apples. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are done.
Delicious topped with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: ice tea slush
directions: Steep tea in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes; remove tea bags and discard.
Stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour in container for freezer and freeze until firm.
Remove about 10 minutes before serving.
Spoon into glasses; garnish with lemon wedges.
Keep unused portion in freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: rio grande pork roast
directions: Place pork (fat side up) on rack in shallow roasting pan. Combine the salt, garlic salt and the first 1/2 teaspoon chili powder; rub into roast.
Roast at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 165°.

title: alice's chocolate fudge
directions: Melt block of chocolate, being careful not to burn (melt slowly).
Add peanut butter; stir.
Add powdered sugar (enough to knead).
Add nuts.
Roll into logs or spread in a pan.
Cut into slices or squares before it hardens.
Store in airtight container. Keeps a long time.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend flour, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Press in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Place 1 pint of strawberries in pie crust.
To the other pint of strawberries, add the sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until clear and thick.
Pour over berries.
Cool and top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and cook on medium heat until rolling boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool until room temperature.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add baking powder and beat, adding 6 tablespoons sugar one at a time until very stiff.
Put meringue on top of pie and brown in oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put water in saucepan.
Add cornstarch and sugar; mix well. Boil until clear.
Add Jell-O; mix until Jell-O is dissolved. Pour over berries; mix.
Put into pie crusts; let set in refrigerator until Jell-O is thick.

title: kim's fruit dip
directions: Mix all in blender.
Serve as a dip for your choice of cut up bananas, apples, grapes, melon slices, etc.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs until well combined.
In a small bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to eggs and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Drain pineapple well.
Add carrots, walnuts and pineapple to batter. Blend to mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 or 10-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake cool on rack.

title: ashley's favorite pound cake
directions: Easy directions:
Put all ingredients in bowl and beat for 20 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° (cold oven) for 1 hour.
After cooling, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: beet borsch(serves 6)
directions: Boil or steam beets about 1 hour or until tender or pressure cook on 15 pounds pressure for 15 minutes.
Reserve liquid. Strain through cheesecloth. Set aside.

title: meatballs in red wine sauce
directions: Mix together first 10 ingredients plus 1 clove garlic; form into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll lightly in flour.
Place salad oil and remaining garlic in large skillet; add meatballs and brown on all sides.

title: tomato and noodles(burrough family favorite dish)
directions: Sift flour
in
a small bowl.
Make a hole in flour and break 1
egg.
With
hands,
work
flour
into
egg until very stiff. Place on board and roll very thin, then leave on board about 15 minutes.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice in real thin slices. Shake
the
flour off and drop in boiling tomato mixture.

title: chili beans
directions: Mix ingredients in crockpot and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 3 servings)
directions: Mix nutmeg, cinnamon, Wesson oil, sugar, eggs and salt.
When thoroughly mixed, add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and pour mixture into cans until each can is approximately 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool cans for 10 minutes, then turn out to finish cooling.
Makes 3 (1 pound) loafs.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together salad oil and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until blended. Add half of dry ingredients.
Mix well and beat in carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Add rest of dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Bake in angel food cake pan or 11 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° until brown and toothpick comes out clean when tested.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: biscuit mix
directions: To make this mix for my pantry shelf, I times it by 4 and store in large jars ready to use in place of store bought biscuit mix (8 cups flour, 4 tablespoons baking powder and 1 1/3 cups Crisco).
Store in a cool place.
Keeps well 2 to 3 months.

title: meal in one bean pot
directions: Rinse beans, removing any pebbles, etc. that might be in the package.
In soup pot, cover the beans with water and heat to a boil.
Turn off heat and cover the pot for about 2 hours.
Add ham bone and cook for about an hour.
Remove the ham bone from beans. If there is any ham left on the bone, add it to the soup pot.
If you are using chopped, cooked ham instead of the ham bone, add it at this time.
Also add the hash browns, tomatoes, butter, and black pepper.
Continue cooking over medium heat until beans are tender.
This will probably take about 30 minutes.
Taste and add salt, if needed.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and dry ingredients.
Form level tablespoons of dough into balls.
Dip one side in sugar and place on pan to bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Dough is very soft and easier to manage if chilled before forming balls.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13 baking pan. Put pineapple and juice and cherry pie filling in pan. Sprinkle cake mix over this. Dot with oleo and pecans. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup and salt to a boil.
Remove from heat and immediately add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper; let cool.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine; pour in sugar and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, egg and pineapple.
Cook until caramelized (1/2 hour).
Don't burn!
Let cool for 10 minutes. Add whipped topping, nuts and apples.
Refrigerate.

title: lou's german slaw
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.
Pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Serves 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook one hour.
Serve over nacho chips, crumbled. Top with sour cream, cheese and black olives.

title: best chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water for chicken broth.
Drain; remove bones.
Cube cooked chicken.
Melt butter and simmer cut up vegetables about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, noodles and cut up chicken.
Simmer until noodles are done.
Add salt and pepper as needed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, adding to mixer in order given.
Pour into a greased and floured baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: french glaze strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and cap strawberries.
Place half of berries in baked pie shell.
Crush the remaining berries and, if necessary, add water to make 1 1/2 cups juice.
Bring to a boil and stir in mixture of sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until clear (boil 1 minute).
Pour mixture over berries in shell and chill at least 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: original girl scout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add flour mixture to butter and sugar, along with eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix well. Chill dough about 1 hour. Roll very thin and use tin can to cut out cookie shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Sprinkle baked cookies with a little sugar. Makes 6-7 dozen cookies.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter cup oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl beat oleo and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, soda and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Stir in oats.
Cover dough; refrigerate several hours, until firm enough to handle.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until almost set; cool 5 minutes.
Remove wrappers from peanut butter cups and place on each cookie, pressing down gently. Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: the i-hate-squash casserole
directions: Saute carrots and onion in a little oil until onion is just translucent.
Cover and let steam for a few minutes.
Mix squash, onion, carrots, sour cream and soup.
Melt butter and toss with stuffing.

title: lasagna
directions: Add oil to boiling water.
Slowly add 3 noodles at a time until all are added.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
In separate pan, brown hamburger; add garlic salt, pepper, oregano, parsley and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sauce to bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Then add 3 or 4 noodles (overlapping), then next layer add Ricotta cheese, then Mozzarella cheese, then sauce. Repeat this process until noodles are gone or pan is full.
With sauce on top, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings or more.

title: orange pralines
directions: Place sugar, cream, salt and corn syrup in a saucepan and stir constantly until mixture boils.
Add orange juice slowly and continue cooking until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240° on candy thermometer.)
Add orange rind and cook until it reaches 240° again.
Add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Cool.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add pecans.
Drop on wax paper. Store in tin or plastic containers.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds of candy.

title: skinny fruit whirl
directions: Whirl all ingredients together in blender until smooth.
Makes about 1 quart.
Mixture may be frozen to make sherbet.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients
together and bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: creamy pimento cheese
directions: Cut cheese in chunks and place in a saucepan on low heat. Melt it.
Stir occasionally.
When almost melted, add beaten egg and mix well.
Remove from heat and add chopped pimento and salad dressing.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator, stays smooth and creamy.
Makes a generous portion.

title: raisin bran applesauce muffins
directions: Pour milk over Raisin Bran; let set 2 minutes and add oil, eggs and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
Bake in well-greased muffin tin for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: mashed potato balls
directions: To leftover mashed potatoes, add chopped onions.
Form into balls.
Roll in melted butter and then in crushed corn flakes. Heat thoroughly in oven.

title: blue ribbon banana cake
directions: Cream shortening in a large mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add banana; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a medium bowl.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup flaked coconut evenly over batter in each cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake layers comes out clean.
Let cake layers cool in pans 10 minutes.
Carefully remove cake layers from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Place one cake layer, coconut side down, on a serving plate.
Spread top of cake layer with Creamy Nut Filling.
Top with remaining layer, coconut side up.
Spread White Snow Frosting on sides and 1-inch around top edge of cake, leaving center unfrosted.
Yield:
one 2-layer cake.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; put in an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cold melon soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: Remove seeds from melon, peel and cut the pulp into cubes. Place pulp, cinnamon and 1/4 cup orange juice in a blender and puree.
Combine remaining orange juice and lime juice.
Stir in the puree.
Chill thoroughly and serve in chilled soup bowls garnished with sprigs of mint.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Cook Creamettes in salted water.
Drain and add the rest.
I cook my celery.
Bake in slow oven for two hours at 250°.
Very good.

title: make a memory game(child-approved)
directions: Young children generally do better than adults when they play memory games, games made of pairs of cards that players must match (similar to the game show "Concentration").
Create your own homemade version using special stickers, pictures and other funny things kids find around the house.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes with water and butter.
When potatoes are tender; add remaining ingredients.
May want to mash some of potatoes to help thicken soup.
If desired thicker, use flour and water to thicken.

title: white barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate chicken in this sauce 24 hours. Baste while grilling.
This makes 1 2/3 cups of sauce.

title: crustless pie
directions: Melt oleo and pour into a pie dish (large). Mix remaining ingredients and add to baking dish. Bake at 350°.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except clams together, then add clams.
Fry in hot grease until brown.

title: sugar-free banana pineapple ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 10-inch tube pan with nonstick spray; set aside.
Into large bowl, sift together flour, Sweet One, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another large bowl, combine oil, 1 egg white, bananas, pineapple, vanilla and liquid fruit sweetener.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients. Stir in walnuts and 1/2 cup raisins.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients altogether; cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Whip egg whites with a little sugar.
Put on top of filling.
Cook in a 325° oven until brown.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Put salt, honey and oil in bowl.
Add scalded milk.
Stir to dissolve.
Add vinegar, egg and water.
Stir in whole wheat flour and let set for 1/2 hour.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to mixture and finish off with rest of flour.
Knead.
Cover with damp cloth and slip in plastic bag.
Let rise until double.
Knead and shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 or 20 minutes longer.
If too dark before done, decrease baking time.

title: ella davis' egg nog
directions: Beat yolks until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; continue beating until sugar is dissolved.
Slowly add liquor and milk. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: the best baked beans(vintage recipe, 1942)
directions: *Browned sugar can be made by adding 1 tablespoon of molasses to white sugar.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt on very low heat in large saucepan.
Heat just until all cheese is melted, stirring occasionally to make sure it is blended well.
Best served as hot dip with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a clean, plastic flowerpot and garden tools.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine lentils and water in kettle or stock pot.
Cook 30 minutes, or until lentils are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer just until carrots are tender.
Check seasonings and serve.

title: hot diggity dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, in a Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles; drain.
Add onion and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over frankfurters in buns.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: savory rice
directions: Shake flour in bag.
Place bag in microwave-safe bowl.
Roll down top of bag.
Add remaining ingredients, except peas, squeeze gently to blend and break up tomatoes.
Close with nylon tie.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in bag.
Cook on high 24 to 27 minutes or until almost done.
Stir in peas.
Cook 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl and garnish with ice ring and fresh fruit.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour pie filling in oblong glass 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling "evenly."
Slice oleo thin to cover.
Sprinkle nuts and oleo.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Let cool.
Spread on Cool Whip to cover.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat 12-inch Dutch oven.
Mix all the ingredients in the oven,
taking
care to coat the potatoes well.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: easy tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini al dente.
Drain.
While still in drainer, pour olive oil over tortellini and sprinkle with black pepper and garlic powder.
Pour tortellini in medium bowl.
Add black olives, peppers and cheese.
Toss lightly; chill before serving.

title: snowballs
directions: Bring dates, brown sugar and margarine or butter to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Add nuts.
Make in balls and roll in coconut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Serve with crackers.

title: nana's fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add to sugar.
Add milk, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir to mix.
Pat into 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill about 10 minutes.
Then cut into squares.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet, dip glass or fork in white or colored sugar and press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: delicious caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in a
large pan.
Add syrup and sugar. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add salt, vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Bake 1 hour in a 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sour cream yellow squash
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water until just tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain slightly and drain again.
Combine with sour cream, 1/4 cup butter, onions, salt and pepper.
Place in a buttered 1 quart casserole.
Mix together bread crumbs and cheese; toss with 3 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle over squash. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Add onion to bacon grease and simmer until clear.
Add brown sugar and tomato sauce; stir well, then add sauerkraut.
Break bacon into pieces and add to the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 35 minutes or more.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 8 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch casseroles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well. Serves 10.
Top with crumbs (canned seasoned crumbs) before you bake.

title: pasta delight
directions: Cook pasta. Drain fruit.
Put juices in saucepan with eggs, sugar and cornstarch. Cook until thick. Add to pasta.
Cool pasta and juices together in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish at least 4 hours. Fold in fruit and Cool Whip.
Add walnuts for decoration.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar; mix in small bowl.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients, then let rise 1 1/2 hours, then make rolls.
Put in pan; let rise 1 1/2 hours or overnight.
Melt butter; brush rolls.
Cook in a 425° oven until done, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cans of soup, undiluted.
Spoon prepared stuffing over soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes to brown.

title: refrigerator rolls with potatoes
directions: *Instant potatoes may be used after prepared.

title: strawberry cream cheese torte
directions: In a spring-form pan, cover the bottom and sides with approximately 2 to 3 packages of ladyfingers.
Set aside.

title: orange honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender and drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add honey, orange juice, sugar and carrots.
Cook on medium head until carrots are glazed.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken into 1 inch pieces.
Saute in butter in large skillet about 5 minutes.
Add milk, water, broccoli, red pepper and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise and cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend corn, milk and sugar.
Add to this the well beaten eggs. Make a paste of the cornstarch and add to the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into eighths.
Combine dry ingredients. Moisten potatoes in water.
Shake in a bag to coat with cheese mixture.
Melt 1/3 cup oleo or butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn over once.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley to serve.

title: olive macaroni salad
directions: Mix well all of above, except last ingredient.
Chill in large bowl or container, covered, while macaroni cooks.
Rinse cooked macaroni briefly.
Cool and stir while cooling (for approximately 5 minutes).
Add macaroni and chill again.
Serve cold.
Add more olive liquid to loosen, if necessary.

title: refried bean appetizer
directions: Spread refried beans in glass baking dish.
Follow with each ingredient as follows:
use corn chips or tortilla chips to dip appetizer.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Mix package of vanilla pudding with 2 cups skim milk, using wire whisk or electric mixer. Add peanut butter (electric mixer works best). Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into baked pie shell. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top or cover top with additional Cool Whip. Refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: japanese chicken over rice
directions: Melt butter in pan, add peppers, onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir fry until onions are transparent.
Add chicken strips. Cook until done.
Add water, mushrooms; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix corn starch in 1/2 c. water.
Add chicken to thicken.
Pour over rice.
Fix rice according to directions on box before you start.

title: zucchini jumbotte
directions: In a large frying pan, place oil; add onion and garlic.
Cook on low flame until onions are wilted.
Add salt, parsley and basil.
Add water, potatoes, pepper and tomatoes.
Cover pot, over low flame, resume cooking.
Check liquid occasionally.
When potatoes are cooked, add zucchini.
Return to heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and serve.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Make crust type bottom of Cheddar cheese.
Brown hamburger in skillet and add pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Put crescent rolls on top and bake at 425° until brown.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Mix dressing, oil, soup mix, preserves and lemon juice.
Put chicken in shallow baking dish and pour mixture over.
Bake for an hour at 350° or until chicken is done.
Very easy. Serves 4.
You can double recipe for larger groups.

title: schaum torte
directions: Beat all ingredients until very stiff.
Bake in large pan, ungreased, for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Take top off and fill with raspberry preserves.
Cover with whipped cream.
Put top back on and serve.
(Top will come off in pieces.)

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in an oblong Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 30 minutes before cutting into bite-size pieces.
Makes 20 squares or serves 8 to 10 as a side dish.

title: wedding salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs and salt. Cook until thick.
Boil macaroni, drain and mix with thickening. Drain oranges, pineapple and cherries. Mix juice with macaroni.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Next day, add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: disappearing marshmallow bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and butter in 3-quart saucepan, medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove and cool to lukewarm.
Add flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add the marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts and mix 5 strokes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: jelly roll
directions: Do not beat; pour in greased cookie sheet with edge.
When done, turn onto dish towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Use any jelly and cover cake.
Roll up from end of towel. Remove to waxed paper with edge down; cover until cool.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef in chunks and drain.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Add sauces to meat and simmer.
Pour macaroni in large casserole dish. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix in meat sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles; let
stand overnight in cold water.
Pack in sterilized jars.
To
each
quart, add 1/8 teaspoon alum, 2 head dill, 1 clove garlic
or
onion
and
hot
red pepper. Combine vinegar, salt and
water
and
bring
to a boil.
Fill jars and put a grape leaf
in
each jar.
Makes 6 to 8 quarts, depending on size of pickles.
Heat jars in canner until water starts to boil.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well and mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Yields 3 cups.

title: lacy pecan cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 10-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until blended.
Keep warm.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls, about 3 inches apart, onto greased baking sheets (place 4 cookies on each).
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Loosen cookies with pancake turner.
Turn over and roll around the handle of a wooden spoon.
Slide off and cool on rack.
Work quickly.
If cookies become too hard to shape, return to oven for 1 minute to soften.
When cooled, store in airtight container.
Makes 32.

title: nachos
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of glass baking dish, then take hamburger that has been cooked and mix it with the salsa and spread it over the cream cheese.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Microwave or bake until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs and flavorings.
Beat well. Add mashed bananas.
Gradually add flour and dry ingredients. Remove beaters and stir in cherries, chocolate chips and nuts. Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into cubes.
Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in small amount of butter, then add to chicken cubes.
Add sour cream, soup and 1/2 tablespoon poppy seed to mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and add to crackers.
Add the rest of poppy seed (1 1/2 tablespoons) to crackers.
Grease casserole dish and pour chicken mixture in dish and spread cracker mixture on top.
Preheat oven to 350° and cook for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's fruit snaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the one egg used later.
Roll dough into rectangle.
Cut into squares.
Brush top with the 1 beaten egg and sprinkle top, then with powdered sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375°.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: pita pocket bread(arabic bread)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Soften yeast in water.
When it is bubbly, stir the yeast mixture into the flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Knead in a bowl, adding more flour or water as necessary.
The dough should be smooth and firm, not stiff. Brush the top of the dough with butter and cover the bowl.
Let the dough rise until doubled in bulk, then punch the dough down and turn it out onto a floured board.
Divide into 12 pieces. Shape into balls and let rest, covered, 10 minutes.

title: pineapple ham dip
directions: Blend deviled ham with cream cheese.
Add pineapple. Refrigerate covered for several hours.

title: shepherd's pie(low calorie)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, coated with nonstick spray, saute ground beef and onion until beef is browned and crumbly.
Drain fat.
Add carrots, mushrooms, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and rosemary.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: raggedy ann cookies
directions: Cream butter and the sugars together well.
Add the unbeaten egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in the sifted flour (with baking powder mixed in).
If desired, chill dough for 1/2 hour or so for easier handling.
Shape into balls to make about a 3-inch cookie.
Place on buttered baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
When cookies cool, frost with the following frosting recipe.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions; saute until crisp and opaque.
Pour half the onions into casserole.
Cover with half of the cheese and half of the crackers.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and then mix peanut butter, butter, sugar and graham crackers; roll into balls.
Freeze and then dip quickly in chocolate.

title: barbara ann's peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients, covered, to 236°.
Stir in nuts. Cook to 280°.
Add butter.
Cook to 300°, stirring.
Stir in vanilla.
Add soda.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Turn pan upside-down on counter.
Tap pan gently with hammer to release brittle.
Break into pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Blend ingredients.
Top with bacon strips in rows.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: self-rising flour(1 pound)
directions: Mix together well.
Store in tightly covered can and use soon.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Mix in large bowl the sugar, beaten eggs and 1 cup cold water. Blend in small bowl the oleo, shortening and 1 cup boiling water (cooled).
Dissolve yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients together and add flour.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer. Roll and cut rolls.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; chop bell pepper, onion and pimento.
Bring to boil sugar, vinegar, Wesson oil, salt, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand at least 4 hours before serving.
Keeps for days.

title: bread & butter pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, both kinds of peppers, and salt in large bowl or roaster. Cover with ice cubes. Set aside about 3 hours. Drain. Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, turmeric, and celery seed. Put over drained vegetables and put on medium heat. Bring to a boil but do not boil. Pack in warm, sterilized jars & seal. Yields about 8 pt.

title: ultimate stuffed potatoes
directions: In saucepan combine soup, sour cream and mustard.
Add broccoli.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes. Serves 4.
Garnish with chopped sweet red peppers if desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake following box directions in 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Place one layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1/2 pudding on top, then 1/2 pie filling and 1/2 of pineapple.
Repeat with other cake layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Melt oleo in jelly roll pan.
Mix 1 egg and box of cake mix in bowl.
Spread over melted oleo.
In another bowl, mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over the cake mix. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box and drain.
Place broccoli in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Remove crust; cut bread in cubes and soak in milk for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix well and strain.
Dredge raisins with flour and add to bread mixture.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in a buttered or caramel lined baking pan and bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: mock bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Have ready a pie plate or six 2/3 cup capacity ramekins or custard cups.
Put butter in pie plate or ramekins to melt.
In a medium bowl, whisk egg, milk, sugar and melted butter until blended.
Stir in granola.
Pour into chosen containers.

Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes for pie plate, 25 minutes for ramekins or until pudding is no longer liquid in center. Check by inserting a knife and pushing some pudding aside. Pudding should jiggle slightly when gently shaken.
Serves 6.

title: sherried wild rice soup
directions: Wash wild rice thoroughly.
Place in a heavy saucepan with salted water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer covered for about 45 minutes until tender but not mushy.
Uncover.
Fluff with fork. Simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Drain excess liquid.

title: ham and vegetables with mostaccioli
directions: Cook pasta according to directions and drain.
In saucepan, combine zucchini, green onion and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer; simmer 4 to 5 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain well.

title: marbled chocolate bars
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar. Stir in 1/4 cup chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls over batter. Cut through batter with a knife to swirl the cream mixture. Sprinkle with the remaining chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Yields 3 dozen.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, green pepper and onion.
Add enough oats (about 2 handfuls) to hold meatballs together.
Place in casserole dish and add 1 jar Kraft "hot" barbecue sauce.
Bake in oven, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini thin.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes and drain well. Add the onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cut up chicken breast. Mix well.
Melt the oleo and mix with Pepperidge Farm dressing. Spread half of dressing mixture in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour the zucchini mixture over the crumbs.
Add remaining crumbs on top.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes (250°).
Topping browns fast, so cover dish with foil the first 20 minutes, then remove foil so top may brown.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and bananas.
Add flour mixture and beat until blended. Add water; blend in well.
Stir in walnuts.
Add batter to greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool completely.

title: pink banana pancakes
directions: Add gelatin to prepared pancake batter in bowl.
Mix gelatin and pancake batter together with spoon until mixture is all the same color.
Gently stir in bananas.
Cook pancakes, following package directions.
Makes 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: *One pound equals 3 3/4 cups, unsifted.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforations. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into center of each rectangle. Pull 4 corners of dough to center of mixture; seal.
Brush tops with butter. Sprinkle with bread crumbs or sesame seed, if desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Drain liquid from cherries (1 cup) and mix with jello.
Add cream cheese and heat mixture until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Mix well and then add Coke.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Boil at medium boil for 12 minutes only.
Be sure to reach boil before counting the 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and beat until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dishes.

title: german plum cake
directions: Put the butter in a bowl that has been rinsed out with very hot water, so the butter will soften slightly.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg and stir briskly until well mixed.
Add the second egg and beat until light.
Add the flour and salt; mix well and spread in deep pie plate or casserole.
Arrange halves of plums, skin side down, on the batter and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream to which a little fruit syrup has been added. Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl.

title: jean's sabbath beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Pressure cook beans with ample water until barely tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain beans and put them in a bean pot with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 4 to 6 hours.
Add water as needed so they won't dry out.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds of peppers.
Cover with boiling water; cook for 5 minutes.
Drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.) Leave peppers whole or cut lengthwise.
Lightly brown ground beef and sausage.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: wild rice chicken soup
directions: Combine broth, water and rice in 3-quart pot and boil. Reduce heat and cover. Simmer 35 to 40 minutes until rice is tender.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Layer all ingredients in Dutch oven according to list. Cover with foil. Bake 4 hours at 250°. When taken from oven, it's ready.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Peel zucchini and slice into about 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle individual slices with salt to your liking.
Heat oil for deep frying.
Mix pancake mix, vinegar and milk.
Dip each zucchini slice in batter and place in hot oil.
Fry until brown (about 1 to 2 minutes).
Better if you only fry about 4 or 5 at a time.
Do not overcrowd fryer.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cherry flakes
directions: Thoroughly cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto crushed corn flakes. Toss lightly to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Top each with maraschino cherry. Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Yield: About 3 dozen.

title: nice and light dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water in bowl.
Stir in yogurt.
Pour into serving dish.
Chill, covered, until firm. Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: In casserole dish, mix chicken and broccoli.
In bowl, mix cheese, mayo and juice.
Pour on top of chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fat-free pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the flour, salt and sugar. Mix well.
On a lightly floured surface, knead the mixture well with your hands.
Roll pieces of the dough into any shapes you like.
Place them on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with the Pam.

title: roast venison
directions: Wash and clean the meat.
Wrap tightly in heavy aluminum foil after seasoning it with all ingredients.
Roast in a heavy roasting pan for 2 to 3 hours in a 325° oven.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cabbage chicken salad
directions: Combine and sprinkle 1 package from the soup mix on top.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Add pork and beans and place in round casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and arrange around outer edge of dish.
Sprinkle cheese over all and bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: mike's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure and put into mixing bowl, shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure, then measure soda and salt.
Sift all together; add to shortening mixture.
Mix all together.
Roll in small balls; put on cookie sheet; spray with Pam.
Flatten with fork.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 8 or 10 minutes; don't overcook.

title: mixed up snack
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salts and Accent and mix well.
Put all other ingredients in a roasting pan and pour butter or margarine mixture over it.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring often.

title: pork tenderloins(yield: approximately 4 servings per tenderloin.)
directions: Line pan with foil and place in tenderloins. In a
small mixing bowl, stir together soy sauce, olive oil, basil, wine, salt, garlic powder and thyme.
Pour over tenderloins, cover and place in refrigerator. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes. Remove tenderloins to another baking pan and cook at 475° for 20 minutes. Serve with Jezebel Sauce.

title: mother's salad
directions: Mix all together and put in a bowl.
Nuts or bananas can be added.
Chill.

title: norwegian christmas cake
directions: Mix warm milk, yeast cake and enough flour to make soft dough. Cream butter and sugar.
Add raisins, citron, currants and candied fruit.
Mix with soft dough.

title: easy moist pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water in Dutch oven until tender.
Drain well.
Mash until smooth.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat until smooth. Place in Pyrex, greased lightly.
Storage time:
2 weeks.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Arrange potatoes and onion over beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread corn and tomatoes over onion and cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chops with stuffing and potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes like a tomato.
Put in bottom of roaster or crock-pot.
Salt and pepper; cover 1/2 way with water.
Take about 1/2 loaf of bread, dry out.
Cook 2 or 3 stalks of celery and 2 cooking onions until done in saucepan.
Crumble bread and mix with poultry seasoning, sage and chicken broth.
Salt to taste.
Put on top of potatoes.
Brown chops in skillet, then add on top of dressing.
Cook at 375° about 1 hour, then simmer.
Cook at 225° for 2 or 3 more hours.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Place all in crock-pot; cover and simmer on low 5 to 6 hours. Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zona's cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Put
on
wax
paper in refrigerator to firm. Roll into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix together sliced apples and sugar.
Set aside 20 minutes or in refrigerator overnight.
Add oil, vanilla, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, egg, nuts and flour.
Pour into floured pan; bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, cream together butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Gradually stir in sifted ingredients. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls (2 inches apart) on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool on wire rack.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Grease (Butter) 13x9x2 baking pan, cut bread into inch thick slices and arrange in one layer in bottom of pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients except butter.
When thoroughly mixed pour over bread in pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
To bake, uncover pan dot with butter and bake at 350 for 45-50 minutes.
Remove, let stand 5 minutes. Serve with maple syrup or honey.

title: fruit on skewers
directions: Place pineapple chunks, apple chunks, banana pieces and grapes on the skewers.
Repeat until you have filled as many as you want. Serve right away.
You can use any fruit you want.

title: montana divinity
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water until it forms a thread. Whip into the stiffly beaten egg whites and let stand.
Boil 3 cups sugar, 1/2 cup water and syrup until it threads.
Pour this last mixture into the first and beat until stiff. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour onto a waxed paper lined large pan and cool.
This is a large recipe.

title: broccoli-cauliflower bake
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed on packages.
Drain. If using the soup, mix soup with vegetables.
If using shredded cheese, layer vegetables with cheese.
Place (or layer) in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart buttered dish.
Melt butter and mix with crushed crackers, using a fork.
Place cracker mix on top of vegetables and cheese.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: steamed cabbage with noodles
directions: Shred cabbage as for coleslaw.
Heat oil in a large frying pan. Add onions; saute 2 to 3 minutes; then shredded cabbage.
Salt and stir.
Cover.
Cabbage will wilt nicely.
Taste.
Add more salt to taste.

title: bean pot
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Cook
in a crock-pot or slowly on top of range until heated thoroughly.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Empty cherries into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread evenly. Squeeze lemon over cherries.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix in oil. Add water and knead, about 3 minutes.
Add pepperoni.
Knead until no longer sticky.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Beat down and put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable gratin with cucumber
directions: Quarter the unpeeled cucumber and then cut each quarter into 1/4 inch slices.
Fry the spring onions and cauliflower in the butter for 5 minutes.
Put the cucumber in the bottom of an ovenproof dish.
Put the fried mixture over the top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix the cheese with the breadcrumbs and put over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: scrumptious fruit!
directions: Pour fruit into large bowl.
Add dry pudding mix.
Stir and chill.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, saut green pepper, onion, celery, carrots and garlic in oil until crisp-tender. Add herbs and spices. Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, bouillon and mushrooms. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in olives, zucchini, chili and garbanzo beans. Add water; simmer until thoroughly heated and zucchini is crisp and tender. Sprinkle cheese over chili when served. Can be served with rice and corn muffins. Makes 8 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup of the noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper.
Put in baking dish, then spread 1 cup noodles over top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Shake well. Pour over salad, add salt and pepper to taste and toss.

title: peachy morning
directions: Pour the milk into the blender and add the yogurt, peaches, cherries, honey and vanilla. Blend on high speed until smooth and serve immediately.

title: bulghur wheat pilaf
directions: Saute the onions and celery in oil until they are light brown and tender.
Add bulghur wheat and continue cooking and stirring until browned.
Add the chicken stock and mix thoroughly.
Cover and allow to simmer for 20 minutes or until the liquid has been absorbed and the wheat is tender.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, then add remaining ingredients. Chill until mixture sets.

title: hunter's stew(method:  one pot)
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix flour with seasoning. Dredge cubes of meat in flour mixture.
Melt butter in kettle. Add onion; cook until tender, but do not brown.
Add cubes of meat and brown.
Add enough water to cover meat; simmer about 3 hours, until meat is tender.
Add more water, if necessary, to prevent burning.
Peel potatoes and quarter.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes during last half hour of cooking.
Add milk to stew (mix milk with flour).
Cook gently until gravy thickens, stirring to prevent burning.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Beat together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add cereals and coconut. The dough will be crumbly.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut or drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet. Press down dough lightly.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind oranges and cranberries in food chopper or blender. Pour in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, apples and nuts.
Prepare jello and add ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Cut salmon with fork.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Form into
a loaf.
Put in a greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. The remaining soup can be diluted slightly with water to make a sauce.

title: grandpa's potatoes
directions: Line a broiler pan with foil and dot the foil with butter. Spread potatoes and onions evenly over the foil.
Cover with a lid of foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
When half done, turn and re-cover until done.
Uncover and let brown or crisp before serving.

title: cheap pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, mix all ingredients except oats.
Mix well.
Add oats.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie is set and golden brown.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Whip the cream, fold into cream cheese.
Thaw strawberries.
With ladyfingers, line bottom and sides of pan (standing up).
Add mixture and cover bottom (ladyfingers, mixture, etc.), repeat.
Mix cornstarch with strawberries while cold.
Add to juice then put strawberries in.
Boil until strawberries thicken.
Keep close watch so as not to burn.
Cool and add to top of cake.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put in deep kettle margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk and bring to boil over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend until peanut butter melts and then add oatmeal and stir in well.
Put on wax paper by spoonfuls and cool.
Store in cans with wax paper between layers.

title: mary's icing
directions: Mix everything together, except Cool Whip. Next add Cool Whip and spread on cake.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients together until smooth.
Have apples ready. Mix together cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Put half of batter in greased tube pan.
Lay half of the apple slices on batter and sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spice scratch cake
directions: Add spices to flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and sugar; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to sugar mixture. Pour into well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or layered pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat soup and add to gelatin. Cool, then add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set in two-quart mold (rubbed with olive oil) several hours.
Makes good dip if only 1/2 package of gelatin is used.
Mousse is great used as a spread for crackers.

title: calamondin marmalade
directions: Cook fruit pulp in water for 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and add sugar.
Return to stove and bring to a boil.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll up into 2 rolls.
Freeze.
Slice thin when ready to bake.
Bake at 350° in a greased pan.

title: enormous greek artichoke salad(servings:  8)
directions: Combine lemon juice, olive oil, oregano, garlic and salt in pint jar.
Tighten lid and shake well.
Let marinate overnight. Re-shake jar just before using.
Dressing will keep refrigerated indefinitely!

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In a large baking dish, arrange the broccoli; place chicken on top.
Drizzle with Butter Buds; sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serving: Calories 288; fat 15 gr.; cholesterol 78 mg.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Saute celery, onions and pepper.
Add broth to crumbled bread.
Add undiluted soup; mix in.
Saute onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Season with sage, ground sage, salt and pepper; mix well.
Do not make stiff.
Use enough broth to give enough moisture to cook.
Add beaten egg to dressing.
Bake in oven at 325° until dressing is done.
Stir while baking.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese; add 1 package dried beef, cut up, and all other ingredients.
Mix very well.
Cut up other package dried beef. Shape cream cheese mixture into ball and roll in beef.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana pudding 2
directions: Mix pudding and milk until blended.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
In a dish put sliced bananas and vanilla wafers.
Pour the pudding over the cookies and bananas.
Chill until read to eat.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix corn starch with 1/2 c. sugar, and salt; slowly stir in water. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon. Beat egg yolks and add remaining 1/2 c. sugar: cook approximately 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in margarine, lemon rind, and juice. Let cool until warm; pour into baked pie shell.

title: pastry crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt with fork or pastry blender. Beat together vinegar, egg and water.
Add this mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until evenly moistened.
Form into a ball and chill about 15 minutes.

title: fruited french muffins
directions: In pie plate, whisk eggs, orange juice, cinnamon-sugar and vanilla.
Add flour muffin halves; turn to coat both sides.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter. Place prepared muffin halves, cut side down, in skillet; cook until lightly browned on both sides, about 5 minutes.
Repeat with remaining muffins, eggs mixture and margarine.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, toss fruit with preserves.
Serve mixture over prepared muffins.
Serves four.

title: strawberry gelatin
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip in large mixing bowl.
Add jello; mix.
Add strawberries and pecans; mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish or one of your choice and refrigerate.
Best when made a day before serving.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Combine sugar, water, apple juice and lemon juice in large container; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add raspberries, sherbet and 7-Up; mix well.
Yield: 25 servings.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: *Add some other pieces of chicken to make your broth have a richer flavor.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions together, then add the remaining ingredients.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix soup and 1/2 can water; heat to boiling.
Let cool.
Mix gelatine with 1/2 cup water.
Mix with soup.
Blend in cream cheese; stir in onions, bell pepper, shrimp and crab meat.
Pour into greased mold.
Refrigerate approximately 4 to 6 hours.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Combine yolks, granulated sugar, lemon juice, rind and butter. Cook in double boiler until mixture thickens. Beat well. Add confectioners sugar if desired.

title: blade steaks and gravy
directions: Pour soup in a bowl. Stir until smooth. (Do not add water.) In a large crock-pot, pour enough soup in to cover bottom of pot. Lay the steaks around in the pot. Cover with remaining soup. Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Mix together thoroughly and use like salt.
Great as seasoning rub on ribs or steaks or brisket for the grill.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; add salad oil slowly, beating constantly.
Continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and mix well.
Store in fridge.
If separates during storage, beat again. Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Serve over fruit.

title: russian tea
directions: Remember, the old folks are worth a fortune...with silver in their hair, gold in their teeth, stones in their kidneys, lead in their feet and gas in their stomaches.

title: spanish balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Shape into balls.	Bake 20 minutes at 350°
or until they start to brown slightly.
Makes 75 to 100 appetizers.	These may be frozen, uncooked.	Thaw 20 minutes before baking.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix peas with all other ingredients, mixing well. either put in a crystal salad bowl or serve on beds of lettuce.

title: egg custard pie or black raspberry pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add salt and milk. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 425° for 15 minutes or until custard is set.

title: beans and ham
directions: Mix together beans and diced ham in a saucepan.
Heat until bubbly and thoroughly warmed.
Serve with cornbread! Serves approximately 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put 3/4 cup water with 1/3 cup rice; boil for 15 minutes.
Add 1 quart milk and 1 cup sugar.
Simmer slowly for about 1 hour. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat 3 eggs, adding 1/4 cup water or milk to eggs, along with a pinch of salt.
Stir until it boils.
Place in a dish to cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix lime and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze.
(Do not take out of freezer until ready to use. Cuts easily; return unused pie to freezer until ready to use again.)

title: liqueur
directions: Pour vodka in jars to cover berries. Let stand as long as possible, 1 to 2 years. For a very smooth berry taste.

title: sour cream strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries (still frozen) and pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into large mold.
Chill until firm while other half remains at room temperature.
Meanwhile, let sour cream come to room temperature. Spread sour cream on top of congealed mixture and top with remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill again until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts together and spread in well-greased Pyrex pie plate.
Scatter chili peppers and spread mayonnaise over artichoke hearts.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; 25 minutes if prepared ahead and refrigerated.
(Do not use the microwave oven; the cheese does not melt nicely.)
Serve with tortilla chips.
This recipe is easy and delicious!

title: pot roast
directions: Heat skillet with oil.
Flour the roast and brown quickly. Put in heavy pot with boiling water. Sprinkle soup mix on top
of roast. Simmer covered on top of stove approximately 2 hours or longer.
Check and add hot water as needed.

title: baked clams
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shells together until well blended. Stuff shells.
Keep a small amount of crumbs on the side and moisten them with olive oil.
Sprinkle these over the tops of the stuffed clams.
Place in preheated oven at 425° for about 16 to 18 minutes until the tops brown.

title: vegetarian chicken salad
directions: Open a can of pear halves; arrange on lettuce leaves.
Top with Miracle Whip.
Garnish with grated American cheese.

title: chili dip
directions: Chop up onion and green pepper.
Then saute onion and green pepper in a small amount of margarine or butter until they are tender.
Add can of chili and catsup to onion and pepper pan. Stir and heat slowly.
Stir in grated Cheddar cheese.
Add Tabasco sauce if desired.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: just for kids soda dough
directions: Mix and stir over medium heat until too thick to stir.
Store in an airtight container.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
in
1	cup boiling water.
Add berries and pineapple.	Put
in
Pyrex	dish
and
congeal.
Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix with sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Spread on top of congealed salad and chill.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Place chicken breasts on plate and cover with plastic wrap; cook in microwave for 12 minutes.
Tear chicken in bite size pieces.
Mix soup, milk and cheese with chicken.
Take the rolls, fold out and fill with mixture.
Roll up, put in pan and cook until rolls are done.

title: min's pie
directions: Beat
sugar
and melted butter together.
Add remaining ingredients; beat eggs in last.
Bake in an uncooked pie shell at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Heat cherries with juice in a saucepan with sugar.
Mix cornstarch with orange juice and add to warm cherries.
Cook until thickened.
Serve warm over ice cream, pound cake or angel food cake.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugars.
Add
eggs, vanilla and water and
blend	well.
Add
sifted
dry
ingredients, except oatmeal, and
mix
well.
Add
oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
(If you wish, you
may
add 2 cups nuts or 2 cups chopped raisins, instead of 1 cup of each.) Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: luscious lime cheesecake
directions: In a food processor, process cheeses until smooth.
In small saucepan, stir together sugar and gelatin.
Whisk in milk over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Pour gelatin mixture through feed tube with food processor running, processing until smooth.
Transfer mixture to medium bowl.
Stir in lime juice, vanilla and lime peel until well blended.
Chill cheese mixture, stirring occasionally, until it mounds when dropped from a spoon, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tomatoes provencale
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel; reserve drippings in skillet.
Set aside.
Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in skillet until tender.
Stir in reserved bacon, flour and seasoned salt.
Set aside.
Cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices. Place half of the slices in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon half of bacon/onion mixture over tomatoes.
